I should still have my Mom!

273
00:10:17,677 --> 00:10:19,044
Hey, hey!

274
00:10:19,078 --> 00:10:20,879
Have you forgotten that
your mother was my wife?

275
00:10:20,913 --> 00:10:22,716
I lost her too!

276
00:10:22,748 --> 00:10:24,116
I lost her!

277
00:10:24,149 --> 00:10:24,917
I'm sorry.

278
00:10:24,950 --> 00:10:26,318
[Daniel] Oh God.

279
00:10:26,352 --> 00:10:27,886
- I'm sorry, Dad, I didn't...
- No, no, no, no.

280
00:10:27,920 --> 00:10:29,421
- Oh, no, no, no, no, no.
- I'm sorry, Dad.

281
00:10:29,455 --> 00:10:31,857
- I'm sorry.
- I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

282
00:10:31,890 --> 00:10:33,158
I'm sorry.

283
00:10:33,192 --> 00:10:34,793
Look, we're all going
through this, alright?

284
00:10:34,827 --> 00:10:36,595
We all lost her.

285
00:10:36,630 --> 00:10:40,032
Lindsey, look, do you
remember that group

286
00:10:40,065 --> 00:10:41,033
the pastor was talking about?

287
00:10:41,066 --> 00:10:42,234
No, please,

288
00:10:42,268 --> 00:10:43,202
- that's not gonna help.
- No, no, no.

289
00:10:43,235 --> 00:10:43,969
No, it's not gonna help.

290
00:10:44,003 --> 00:10:44,937
It won't bring Mom back.

291
00:10:44,970 --> 00:10:47,206
No, but it can't hurt either.

292
00:10:48,807 --> 00:10:49,775
Look, no, listen,

293
00:10:50,876 --> 00:10:52,077
your heart is so pained,

294
00:10:52,111 --> 00:10:53,279
your mother would never
want you to feel this way.

295
00:10:53,312 --> 00:10:54,681
Please, just go for me.

296
00:10:54,714 --> 00:10:56,716
Just go, please,
just once, just once.

297
00:10:56,750 --> 00:10:57,751
- Please, okay?
- Fine.

298
00:10:59,418 --> 00:11:00,754
But I wanna do this on my own.

299
00:11:03,757 --> 00:11:04,556
Okay.

300
00:11:07,126 --> 00:11:08,762
Let me drive, okay?

301
00:11:10,996 --> 00:11:11,964
- Okay.
- Come on.

302
00:11:16,670 --> 00:11:19,605
[Lindsey sniffles]

303
00:11:20,506 --> 00:11:23,509
[elevator rumbling]

304
00:11:27,846 --> 00:11:29,615
[John] How's your
week been, Ava?

305
00:11:29,649 --> 00:11:30,416
[Ava] Good.

306
00:11:30,449 --> 00:11:31,685
[John] That's good.

307
00:11:31,718 --> 00:11:33,152
We're glad to see
you back again.

308
00:11:33,185 --> 00:11:34,486
Yeah, it's been a, it's
been a wonderful week.

309
00:11:34,520 --> 00:11:36,221
We had a lot going
on with the church.

310
00:11:36,255 --> 00:11:37,956
And, yeah, so we're very excited

311
00:11:37,990 --> 00:11:40,760
to have those special activity
things lined up as well,

312
00:11:40,794 --> 00:11:42,696
so it's always fun with them.

313
00:11:42,729 --> 00:11:43,829
Ricky, how've you
been this week?

314
00:11:43,862 --> 00:11:45,431
For those of you
just joining us,

315
00:11:45,464 --> 00:11:47,032
I'd like to tell you a
bit about what we do here

316
00:11:47,066 --> 00:11:48,668
in the group.

317
00:11:48,702 --> 00:11:52,739
Our grief support group is a
place of healing and of hope.

318
00:11:52,772 --> 00:11:54,741
We like to remember our
loved ones out loud.

319
00:11:54,774 --> 00:11:57,843
We share stories, we share
memories good and bad,

320
00:11:57,876 --> 00:11:59,912
but more importantly,
we support each other

321
00:11:59,945 --> 00:12:01,781
through the sadness of loss,

322
00:12:01,815 --> 00:12:04,283
and we move into the
comfort of knowing

323
00:12:04,316 --> 00:12:08,220
that they remain in our hearts
and our memories forever.

324
00:12:09,388 --> 00:12:10,956
Now, I'd like to
have our new members

325
00:12:10,989 --> 00:12:12,124
go ahead and
introduce themselves,

326
00:12:12,157 --> 00:12:13,793
then we'll share some stories.

327
00:12:15,060 --> 00:12:17,396
Would you like to go first?

328
00:12:18,897 --> 00:12:21,200
Hi, I'm Lindsey.

329
00:12:21,233 --> 00:12:23,535
I lost my mom a few months ago.

330
00:12:25,604 --> 00:12:26,405
Hi, Lindsey.

331
00:12:26,438 --> 00:12:27,774
We're happy to meet you.

332
00:12:27,807 --> 00:12:29,174
Thank you for being here.

333
00:12:29,208 --> 00:12:30,576
And how about you?

334
00:12:31,678 --> 00:12:34,748
Hi, I'm, I'm Andrew.

335
00:12:34,781 --> 00:12:37,449
I lost my brother in a car
accident about a year ago,

336
00:12:37,483 --> 00:12:40,586
and things haven't
really gotten better,

337
00:12:40,619 --> 00:12:43,055
so my mom recommended I
come to a support group.

338
00:12:44,123 --> 00:12:45,725
Well, thank you, Andrew.

339
00:12:45,759 --> 00:12:47,694
At the very least, we hope you
can find some comfort here,

340
00:12:47,727 --> 00:12:49,261
and know you're not alone.

341
00:12:49,294 --> 00:12:50,864
Thank you.

342
00:12:50,896 --> 00:12:53,767
So, would anyone like to
begin by sharing a story?

343
00:12:54,868 --> 00:12:56,235
I'd like to share
my story, John.

344
00:12:56,268 --> 00:12:57,569
[John] Oh, Ava, please.

345
00:12:59,773 --> 00:13:03,108
My husband and I were trying
to have a baby for so long.

346
00:13:04,376 --> 00:13:06,880
We thought after IVF and
for trying for so long

347
00:13:06,912 --> 00:13:08,380
that it would never happen,

348
00:13:09,883 --> 00:13:11,885
but we were happy because
we knew that we had options.

349
00:13:14,620 --> 00:13:19,626
One night we went to a restaurant
with my husband's boss.

350
00:13:20,959 --> 00:13:23,128
It was this restaurant
on the top of a building,

351
00:13:23,162 --> 00:13:24,430
really high up.

352
00:13:24,463 --> 00:13:25,899
Now, I don't do heights,
[gentle music]

353
00:13:25,931 --> 00:13:28,635
so I got really sick.

354
00:13:29,601 --> 00:13:31,036
It was so embarrassing.

355
00:13:33,840 --> 00:13:36,776
The next night I was still sick.

356
00:13:36,810 --> 00:13:39,813
I mean, every smell, just about
anything made me feel sick.

357
00:13:41,580 --> 00:13:43,215
He knew I was pregnant,

358
00:13:43,248 --> 00:13:46,552
but I was like, "No,
I mean, it can't be."

359
00:13:46,585 --> 00:13:48,220
He went out, he
bought me a test,

360
00:13:48,253 --> 00:13:50,589
and it turns out he was
right, I was pregnant.

361
00:13:52,257 --> 00:13:53,927
We were so happy.

362
00:13:56,128 --> 00:13:58,263
I mean, it was probably one
of the second best moments

363
00:13:58,297 --> 00:13:59,131
of our lives.

364
00:14:00,566 --> 00:14:03,435
Our first was when
our baby boy was born.

365
00:14:04,637 --> 00:14:06,004
It was pure joy.

366
00:14:07,707 --> 00:14:08,942
Our family was complete.

367
00:14:13,111 --> 00:14:17,149
A week later, he went
on a business trip,

368
00:14:17,182 --> 00:14:20,552
and the plane crashed,

369
00:14:20,586 --> 00:14:21,688
and he didn't make it.

370
00:14:25,357 --> 00:14:27,326
But he got to meet Ryan Junior.

371
00:14:29,428 --> 00:14:31,931
[John] Ava, thank you so
much for sharing that story.

372
00:14:31,965 --> 00:14:32,799
You're welcome.

373
00:14:34,600 --> 00:14:39,605
It's hard, but I realized
through the process of healing,

374
00:14:43,141 --> 00:14:46,178
there are more good memories
than there could ever be bad.

375
00:14:50,215 --> 00:14:54,353
I just wish that I could
hear him again, or see him.

376
00:14:57,657 --> 00:14:58,457
Thank you.

377
00:15:02,361 --> 00:15:05,364
Would any of our new members
like to share a story?

378
00:15:09,769 --> 00:15:10,770
I'm not ready yet.

379
00:15:11,838 --> 00:15:12,672
That's okay.

380
00:15:13,773 --> 00:15:15,574
When you're ready,
we'll be here.

381
00:15:15,607 --> 00:15:17,276
You know, remembering
our loved ones out loud

382
00:15:17,309 --> 00:15:20,245
is greatly helpful.

383
00:15:20,279 --> 00:15:21,313
[gentle music]

384
00:15:21,346 --> 00:15:22,982
It keeps them in our hearts.

385
00:15:24,383 --> 00:15:26,986
Andrew, would you like to share?

386
00:15:27,987 --> 00:15:29,889
I guess, yeah, yeah.

387
00:15:29,923 --> 00:15:30,723
Yeah, I'll go.

388
00:15:32,357 --> 00:15:35,294
But it's kind of hard to
remember things right now.

389
00:15:38,263 --> 00:15:42,534
No good memories, no bad
ones, just, it just all sucks.

390
00:15:45,103 --> 00:15:48,473
You know, I was in that car
accident where my brother died.

391
00:15:50,175 --> 00:15:51,711
Why not me?

392
00:15:51,744 --> 00:15:53,846
What makes me so special?

393
00:15:53,880 --> 00:15:54,681
He was my brother.

394
00:15:54,714 --> 00:15:55,480
He was my twin.

395
00:15:55,514 --> 00:15:56,683
He was a part of me.

396
00:16:00,053 --> 00:16:02,021
We were supposed to
travel the world together,

397
00:16:02,055 --> 00:16:03,455
and now it's just me,

398
00:16:05,290 --> 00:16:06,926
and that ain't right.

399
00:16:09,062 --> 00:16:12,031
Andrew, it's,
it's not just you.

400
00:16:12,065 --> 00:16:14,499
You know, he's
still part of you,

401
00:16:14,533 --> 00:16:16,401
and remembering him
is gonna help you.

402
00:16:18,938 --> 00:16:20,039
Thank you for sharing.

403
00:16:21,139 --> 00:16:22,574
[Lindsey] Pastor John?

404
00:16:22,608 --> 00:16:24,276
[John] Yes, Lindsey.

405
00:16:24,309 --> 00:16:26,713
Could I tell a little
about my mom, maybe?

406
00:16:26,746 --> 00:16:28,113
Yes, I think we'd love that.

407
00:16:30,750 --> 00:16:32,150
My last memory of her,

408
00:16:32,184 --> 00:16:33,886
she was helping me
pick out my dress

409
00:16:33,920 --> 00:16:35,487
for my first school dance.

410
00:16:38,256 --> 00:16:41,094
My mom was so sweet,
always loving.

411
00:16:43,730 --> 00:16:46,633
Her dream was to be there
for me at my wedding,

412
00:16:51,136 --> 00:16:53,138
but now she won't be able to.

413
00:16:58,811 --> 00:17:00,880
I'm sorry, I can't
talk about this yet.

414
00:17:01,814 --> 00:17:02,715
And that's okay.

415
00:17:02,749 --> 00:17:04,349
Thank you so much for sharing.

416
00:17:04,383 --> 00:17:06,119
You know, the healing
process takes time.

417
00:17:06,151 --> 00:17:09,488
And Lindsey, when you're
ready, we'll be here to listen.

418
00:17:12,157 --> 00:17:15,061
Well, I think that's a
good place to leave it.

419
00:17:15,094 --> 00:17:17,830
We do have some flyers
over on the table there.

420
00:17:17,864 --> 00:17:20,833
It has some fun activities
to help the healing process.

421
00:17:20,867 --> 00:17:22,467
And before we go,

422
00:17:22,501 --> 00:17:25,504
I'd like you do a
little bit of homework

423
00:17:25,537 --> 00:17:27,172
for this, this next week.

424
00:17:27,205 --> 00:17:30,242
Now, before you look at me
like that, it's nothing hard.

425
00:17:30,275 --> 00:17:33,211
I'd like you to talk to a
relative or a mutual friend,

426
00:17:33,245 --> 00:17:37,016
and have them share a
good memory with you.

427
00:17:37,050 --> 00:17:37,950
I'd like you to write it down,

428
00:17:37,984 --> 00:17:40,153
and if you feel comfortable,

429
00:17:40,185 --> 00:17:41,988
share it when you
come back next week,

430
00:17:42,021 --> 00:17:43,756
and we'll start on
our memory books.

431
00:17:45,257 --> 00:17:47,026
Alright?

432
00:17:47,060 --> 00:17:48,393
Thanks again for
coming everybody.

433
00:17:48,427 --> 00:17:50,863
Remember, there are some
flyers over by the coffee,

434
00:17:50,897 --> 00:17:52,131
that have some
recommended reading.

435
00:17:52,165 --> 00:17:54,167
As always, if you need
to talk to me at all,

436
00:17:55,168 --> 00:17:56,535
feel free to come find me.

437
00:17:57,837 --> 00:17:58,738
Have a wonderful week.

438
00:18:04,576 --> 00:18:07,013
Chocolate chip was
Matthew's favorite cookie.

439
00:18:09,749 --> 00:18:12,284
Hey, I'm sorry
about your brother.

440
00:18:12,317 --> 00:18:13,186
Thanks.

441
00:18:14,219 --> 00:18:16,189
Sorry about your mother too.

442
00:18:16,221 --> 00:18:19,158
Guess we all gotta lose
someone at some point.

443
00:18:19,192 --> 00:18:21,393
Yeah, but it
doesn't feel fair.

444
00:18:21,426 --> 00:18:22,260
I know.

445
00:18:24,030 --> 00:18:26,199
Were you close
to your brother?

446
00:18:26,231 --> 00:18:29,601
Yeah, we were pretty
much like the same person.

447
00:18:31,204 --> 00:18:33,706
We even had our own way
of talking to each other.

448
00:18:33,740 --> 00:18:35,208
Yeah, I've heard that,

449
00:18:35,240 --> 00:18:37,210
that twins can have their
own secret language.

450
00:18:37,242 --> 00:18:38,978
That's actually really cool.

451
00:18:39,011 --> 00:18:41,214
Yeah, yeah, guess so.

452
00:18:42,280 --> 00:18:44,751
Well, I gotta go,
my dad's waiting.

453
00:18:44,784 --> 00:18:47,053
But it was nice to meet you.
[hopeful music]

454
00:18:47,086 --> 00:18:50,255
Hey, I hope you come back.

455
00:18:52,692 --> 00:18:53,525
I think I will.

456
00:18:59,799 --> 00:19:02,735
[Daniel] Ugh, it's
a hot day today, man.

457
00:19:02,769 --> 00:19:04,203
Hey, you alright?

458
00:19:08,241 --> 00:19:10,143
No, seriously, you okay?

459
00:19:10,176 --> 00:19:15,148
I don't know.

460
00:19:16,215 --> 00:19:17,549
What's wrong?

461
00:19:18,517 --> 00:19:19,719
I don't know.

462
00:19:19,752 --> 00:19:21,586
Alright, you
wanna talk about it?

463
00:19:21,620 --> 00:19:23,189
Why?

464
00:19:23,222 --> 00:19:24,257
It won't bring Mom back!

465
00:19:25,557 --> 00:19:28,995
No, but it's nice
to remember her.

466
00:19:30,295 --> 00:19:32,999
Lindsey says Mom is living
in heaven now with God.

467
00:19:33,032 --> 00:19:34,867
I just wish I could
talk to her, Dad.

468
00:19:34,901 --> 00:19:38,237
It would be so nice if
a text or phone call

469
00:19:38,271 --> 00:19:40,405
could reach all the
way up to heaven.

470
00:19:40,438 --> 00:19:41,274
I know.

471
00:19:42,642 --> 00:19:44,442
Look, I knew someone that
wrote a message in a-

472
00:19:44,476 --> 00:19:46,646
- I don't want that, I want Mom!

473
00:19:46,679 --> 00:19:48,815
I want Mom too, okay?

474
00:19:48,848 --> 00:19:50,683
I'm sorry things have changed.

475
00:19:51,951 --> 00:19:54,220
Dad, I don't wanna hike today.

476
00:19:54,253 --> 00:19:55,420
I just wanna go back home.

477
00:19:56,289 --> 00:19:58,191
Right, you don't wanna hike?

478
00:19:58,224 --> 00:19:59,424
You just wanna go home?

479
00:19:59,457 --> 00:20:00,893
Yeah.

480
00:20:00,927 --> 00:20:02,261
Watch a movie with me?

481
00:20:02,295 --> 00:20:03,296
Sure.

482
00:20:04,297 --> 00:20:05,765
It's hot anyway, right?

483
00:20:05,798 --> 00:20:06,966
Come on, come on.

484
00:20:16,508 --> 00:20:21,513
[rain pattering]
[gentle guitar music]

485
00:20:28,254 --> 00:20:30,723
[Daniel sighs]

486
00:20:32,424 --> 00:20:34,392
I'm having a real
hard time here, Abby.

487
00:20:40,565 --> 00:20:42,068
The kids are so sad.

488
00:20:44,337 --> 00:20:46,339
I'm just trying to
make them feel loved.

489
00:20:54,146 --> 00:20:57,884
Just don't laugh at me if
I start to cry. [laughs]

490
00:20:59,318 --> 00:21:00,686
You know, I remember
you saying once

491
00:21:00,720 --> 00:21:03,189
that real men do cry.

492
00:21:06,359 --> 00:21:07,727
Well, this man cries for you.

493
00:21:09,862 --> 00:21:10,663
I love you, Abby.

494
00:21:12,064 --> 00:21:15,268
[gentle guitar music]

495
00:21:28,446 --> 00:21:30,116
Oh, man.
[hopeful music]

496
00:21:30,149 --> 00:21:32,385
Those cookies smell great.

497
00:21:32,417 --> 00:21:34,387
If it's cookies,
you know it's for me.

498
00:21:34,419 --> 00:21:35,420
Every kid loves cookies.

499
00:21:35,453 --> 00:21:37,489
Dad, it's for group.

500
00:21:37,522 --> 00:21:38,357
[Daniel And Josh] Oh.

501
00:21:38,391 --> 00:21:39,926
Can we just have one?

502
00:21:39,959 --> 00:21:41,193
Just one?

503
00:21:41,227 --> 00:21:43,863
Not unless you come
to group with me.

504
00:21:43,896 --> 00:21:44,664
Good luck.

505
00:21:47,400 --> 00:21:49,368
This is a real nice
thing you're doing here.

506
00:21:49,402 --> 00:21:50,403
Thanks, Dad.

507
00:21:51,737 --> 00:21:53,406
How about one for the old man?

508
00:21:55,641 --> 00:21:56,441
Want an apple?

509
00:21:59,979 --> 00:22:01,380
Sure.

510
00:22:01,414 --> 00:22:05,418
[Daniel and Lindsey chuckling]

511
00:22:22,835 --> 00:22:25,271
Andrew, this is my
little brother, Josh.

512
00:22:25,304 --> 00:22:26,272
Josh, meet Andrew.

513
00:22:27,807 --> 00:22:29,175
Hey, Josh.

514
00:22:29,208 --> 00:22:31,243
So, you're the reason

515
00:22:31,277 --> 00:22:34,413
my sister won't let me have
any cookies, aren't you?

516
00:22:34,447 --> 00:22:35,414
Me?

517
00:22:36,682 --> 00:22:38,417
Well, nice to meet
you too, Josh.

518
00:22:41,053 --> 00:22:43,089
I'm gonna go sit down.

519
00:22:43,122 --> 00:22:44,290
You can stop now.

520
00:22:44,323 --> 00:22:45,825
I'm just messing
with you, little man.

521
00:22:45,858 --> 00:22:47,259
Coming to a good spot.

522
00:22:47,293 --> 00:22:48,593
Place helps me out a lot.

523
00:22:48,627 --> 00:22:50,396
[Josh] Sure.

524
00:22:50,429 --> 00:22:52,331
How's your week been?

525
00:22:52,365 --> 00:22:53,232
I've had a good week.

526
00:22:53,265 --> 00:22:54,000
Did you have a good week?

527
00:22:54,033 --> 00:22:55,401
Yeah, it was.

528
00:22:55,434 --> 00:22:57,103
My dad set up to scholarship
in my mom's name,

529
00:22:57,136 --> 00:22:58,971
and we met a few
of the recipients.

530
00:22:59,005 --> 00:23:00,373
Oh, that's cool.

531
00:23:00,406 --> 00:23:02,074
Yeah, it really was.

532
00:23:05,378 --> 00:23:07,446
Hey, you wanna go
get coffee sometime?

533
00:23:07,480 --> 00:23:11,951
Maybe talk about your mother,
or my brother, or the weather?

534
00:23:11,984 --> 00:23:13,252
Yeah, I'd like that.

535
00:23:13,285 --> 00:23:15,287
Maybe you can meet my
best friend, Katie.

536
00:23:15,321 --> 00:23:16,689
Yeah, yeah, that'd be cool.

537
00:23:17,690 --> 00:23:19,025
Okay, let's go.

538
00:23:19,058 --> 00:23:19,859
Yeah.

539
00:23:22,728 --> 00:23:23,796
Alright, everyone.

540
00:23:23,829 --> 00:23:24,764
Well, let's go ahead
and take our seats,

541
00:23:24,797 --> 00:23:25,563
and we can begin.

542
00:23:27,599 --> 00:23:30,469
It's always nice to see
new faces in the group.

543
00:23:30,503 --> 00:23:31,637
And as a little reminder,

544
00:23:31,670 --> 00:23:34,340
I like to say what it
is we do in this group.

545
00:23:35,674 --> 00:23:38,277
Our grief support group is
a place of healing and hope.

546
00:23:38,310 --> 00:23:39,478
[gentle music]

547
00:23:39,512 --> 00:23:42,481
We like to remember our
loved ones out loud.

548
00:23:42,515 --> 00:23:46,152
We share stories, we share
memories, good and bad,

549
00:23:46,185 --> 00:23:48,387
and more importantly, we
like to support each other,

550
00:23:48,421 --> 00:23:51,057
as we move from the
sadness of loss,

551
00:23:51,090 --> 00:23:52,525
to finding the comfort

552
00:23:52,557 --> 00:23:55,027
of knowing that our loved
ones reside in our hearts

553
00:23:55,061 --> 00:23:56,395
and our memories forever.

554
00:23:57,562 --> 00:23:59,532
I'd like the new
faces in the group

555
00:23:59,564 --> 00:24:00,866
to go ahead and
introduce themselves.

556
00:24:00,900 --> 00:24:03,202
And we'll go ahead and
start sharing some stories.

557
00:24:03,235 --> 00:24:08,240
My name's Josh and
my sister made me come.

558
00:24:09,308 --> 00:24:10,242
Well, it's good
to see you, Josh.

559
00:24:10,276 --> 00:24:11,410
Thank you for coming.

560
00:24:11,444 --> 00:24:12,545
Thanks for bringing
him, Lindsey.

561
00:24:12,577 --> 00:24:13,379
And?

562
00:24:15,114 --> 00:24:17,016
Hi, my name is Carrie.

563
00:24:17,917 --> 00:24:20,086
I lost my baby boy.

564
00:24:21,287 --> 00:24:22,521
He had cancer.

565
00:24:23,923 --> 00:24:25,257
Hi, Carrie.

566
00:24:25,291 --> 00:24:26,492
I really hope both of you

567
00:24:26,525 --> 00:24:28,227
can find some comfort
in being here with us.

568
00:24:29,462 --> 00:24:30,763
Carrie, would you like
to share a little more

569
00:24:30,796 --> 00:24:31,997
about your story?

570
00:24:32,031 --> 00:24:33,532
No pressure.

571
00:24:33,566 --> 00:24:35,901
No, I'm not ready.

572
00:24:35,935 --> 00:24:39,738
It's, it's hard to
talk about still.

573
00:24:41,107 --> 00:24:42,308
We're glad you're here.

574
00:24:42,341 --> 00:24:44,577
If you need to talk,
I'm always here.

575
00:24:46,312 --> 00:24:49,081
I lost my mom not too long ago,

576
00:24:49,115 --> 00:24:50,683
and I know it's not the same,

577
00:24:50,716 --> 00:24:53,586
but this group is
really helping me.

578
00:24:55,221 --> 00:24:56,589
Thank you, Lindsey.

579
00:24:56,621 --> 00:24:58,224
Whatever we can do to help,

580
00:24:58,257 --> 00:24:59,391
that's why we're here.

581
00:25:00,493 --> 00:25:02,695
So, everyone, how's
the week been?

582
00:25:06,665 --> 00:25:07,633
It's been better.

583
00:25:11,670 --> 00:25:14,740
My mother and I went
to see my dad's grave.

584
00:25:16,609 --> 00:25:20,613
So, well, she decided
to start a scholarship

585
00:25:24,450 --> 00:25:25,451
in his name, so.

586
00:25:27,653 --> 00:25:28,521
That's wonderful,

587
00:25:28,554 --> 00:25:30,422
and I'm sure he'd be very proud.

588
00:25:30,456 --> 00:25:31,724
Thank you for sharing, Ricky.

589
00:25:32,658 --> 00:25:34,426
How's your week been, Ava?

590
00:25:34,460 --> 00:25:37,596
Oh, mine, mine actually
has been really good.

591
00:25:37,631 --> 00:25:39,465
I've had more good
days than bad,

592
00:25:39,498 --> 00:25:41,267
which I never
thought would happen.

593
00:25:42,668 --> 00:25:44,336
We're actually planning a
trip to see Ryan's parents

594
00:25:44,370 --> 00:25:45,204
this weekend, so.

595
00:25:46,505 --> 00:25:48,674
[John] That sounds
like a wonderful trip.

596
00:25:49,675 --> 00:25:52,011
Yeah, I might be
missing a few meetings.

597
00:25:52,044 --> 00:25:53,779
Oh, well, that's okay.

598
00:25:53,812 --> 00:25:54,980
Certainly a good reason.

599
00:25:55,014 --> 00:25:55,781
Yeah.

600
00:25:55,814 --> 00:25:57,016
[John chuckling]

601
00:25:57,049 --> 00:25:58,984
Andy, how's your
week been, sir?

602
00:26:01,720 --> 00:26:05,624
You know, I'm still
having a hard time.

603
00:26:05,659 --> 00:26:09,261
You know, sometimes I still
feel angry about it all,

604
00:26:09,295 --> 00:26:11,597
him dying and me surviving.

605
00:26:11,631 --> 00:26:15,301
But my mom was actually
going through his stuff,

606
00:26:15,334 --> 00:26:17,637
and she found this dictionary.

607
00:26:17,671 --> 00:26:19,338
It's the dictionary,
we used to use it,

608
00:26:19,371 --> 00:26:21,507
to make our own language.

609
00:26:22,676 --> 00:26:24,644
When I looked at it,
something clicked.

610
00:26:24,678 --> 00:26:26,545
Just realized he
was a part of me.

611
00:26:28,013 --> 00:26:30,382
[John] And how has that
impacted your healing?

612
00:26:30,416 --> 00:26:33,252
Well, I can at
least talk about him.

613
00:26:33,285 --> 00:26:35,554
You know, that's
a big step for me.

614
00:26:35,588 --> 00:26:36,855
That's a great start.

615
00:26:36,889 --> 00:26:41,160
You know, continuing to
remember our loved ones out loud

616
00:26:41,193 --> 00:26:43,796
is always so helpful, you know?

617
00:26:43,829 --> 00:26:45,497
It keeps them right
in our hearts.

618
00:26:45,531 --> 00:26:46,700
Yeah.

619
00:26:46,732 --> 00:26:48,367
It hasn't been easy,
but I've been trying.

620
00:26:49,368 --> 00:26:50,603
Lindsay, how you been?

621
00:26:51,671 --> 00:26:53,572
Honestly, I'm okay.

622
00:26:53,606 --> 00:26:56,342
You know, I know my
mom's always with me,

623
00:26:56,375 --> 00:27:00,714
and my dad and I, we did
some things in her memory.

624
00:27:02,248 --> 00:27:04,383
And I guess I'm just not
as angry as I was before.

625
00:27:07,286 --> 00:27:08,520
That's great to hear.

626
00:27:08,554 --> 00:27:10,289
I'm happy to hear
with your progress.

627
00:27:11,190 --> 00:27:12,626
I'm really proud of all of you.

628
00:27:12,659 --> 00:27:16,395
You know, these, these
reports are great, you know?

629
00:27:16,428 --> 00:27:18,897
I'd actually like to
take a time of prayer.

630
00:27:19,765 --> 00:27:20,966
Bow our heads in prayer.

631
00:27:24,770 --> 00:27:27,039
Heavenly father, we thank you

632
00:27:27,072 --> 00:27:29,241
for this wonderful
night you've given us.

633
00:27:30,309 --> 00:27:31,610
Thank you for reminding us

634
00:27:31,645 --> 00:27:33,879
that your mercies
are new every day.

635
00:27:33,912 --> 00:27:34,913
It says in the book of Matthew,

636
00:27:34,947 --> 00:27:37,449
that blessed are
those who mourn,

637
00:27:37,483 --> 00:27:38,817
for they will be shown mercy.

638
00:27:40,085 --> 00:27:42,788
We pray that your grace
continuously follows us

639
00:27:42,821 --> 00:27:44,423
through our day.

640
00:27:44,456 --> 00:27:46,726
And we pray that
you bless our going

641
00:27:46,760 --> 00:27:49,094
as you blessed our
coming here tonight.

642
00:27:49,128 --> 00:27:50,029
Thank you.

643
00:27:50,062 --> 00:27:52,097
It's in your name we pray.

644
00:27:52,131 --> 00:27:52,931
Amen.

645
00:27:57,002 --> 00:28:00,172
[upbeat guitar music]

646
00:28:05,177 --> 00:28:06,278
Dad, Dad.

647
00:28:06,312 --> 00:28:07,179
[Daniel] Yeah.

648
00:28:07,212 --> 00:28:08,180
Teach me to play guitar.

649
00:28:09,315 --> 00:28:10,549
What now?

650
00:28:10,582 --> 00:28:11,685
Yeah, I wanna write
songs like you do.

651
00:28:11,718 --> 00:28:12,518
Look.

652
00:28:13,619 --> 00:28:14,620
What have you got?

653
00:28:14,654 --> 00:28:17,556
[strings twanging]

654
00:28:18,624 --> 00:28:20,660
[chuckles] This is pretty good.

655
00:28:20,694 --> 00:28:23,763
Yeah, it's for Mom.

656
00:28:23,797 --> 00:28:24,764
You know what,
here, you got it.

657
00:28:24,798 --> 00:28:26,498
Here, give me that guitar.

658
00:28:26,532 --> 00:28:27,866
Take the old man's guitar.

659
00:28:27,900 --> 00:28:30,602
Do you remember that E minor
chord that I showed you

660
00:28:30,637 --> 00:28:31,370
- a while back?
- Yeah.

661
00:28:31,403 --> 00:28:32,237
Yeah?

662
00:28:32,271 --> 00:28:33,038
Let's see what you got.

663
00:28:34,206 --> 00:28:34,973
Here, take the pick.

664
00:28:35,007 --> 00:28:35,874
Try that.

665
00:28:35,908 --> 00:28:36,810
[strings twanging]

666
00:28:36,842 --> 00:28:38,177
Yeah, you're right on the mark.

667
00:28:38,210 --> 00:28:38,977
Let's do another one.

668
00:28:39,011 --> 00:28:40,212
Do you remember D7?

669
00:28:41,613 --> 00:28:42,915
Yeah, one there.

670
00:28:42,948 --> 00:28:44,850
Actually, no, put
this finger up here.

671
00:28:45,851 --> 00:28:46,985
Hit that.

672
00:28:47,019 --> 00:28:48,822
See how that works?
[strings twanging]

673
00:28:48,854 --> 00:28:49,922
Not bad, could be better.

674
00:28:49,955 --> 00:28:52,991
- [Daniel laughs]
- Very good!

675
00:28:53,025 --> 00:28:55,829
[gentle music]

676
00:28:57,797 --> 00:29:00,065
Hey, there you go.

677
00:29:00,099 --> 00:29:01,200
Thank you.

678
00:29:01,233 --> 00:29:03,569
Of course, you're welcome.

679
00:29:03,602 --> 00:29:07,841
So, did you enjoy
group last time?

680
00:29:07,873 --> 00:29:10,075
I dunno, I'm starting
to really like it.

681
00:29:10,109 --> 00:29:11,678
Like, it's helping me.

682
00:29:11,711 --> 00:29:12,846
Me too.

683
00:29:12,878 --> 00:29:14,880
I didn't think I could
stop feeling angry

684
00:29:14,913 --> 00:29:16,014
or guilty about it all,

685
00:29:16,048 --> 00:29:18,217
but little by little, I am.

686
00:29:18,250 --> 00:29:19,985
That's good.

687
00:29:20,018 --> 00:29:21,086
Oh, there's Katie.

688
00:29:22,221 --> 00:29:23,122
Katie's here.

689
00:29:23,155 --> 00:29:25,891
Hi.

690
00:29:25,924 --> 00:29:26,892
Hey, Katie.

691
00:29:26,925 --> 00:29:27,727
Hi, hi.

692
00:29:30,062 --> 00:29:32,197
Katie, this is
Andrew from group.

693
00:29:32,231 --> 00:29:35,167
Andrew, this is Katie,
from like my whole life.

694
00:29:35,200 --> 00:29:36,168
[Andrew] Hi,
hi, how you doing?

695
00:29:36,201 --> 00:29:37,436
[Katie] Hi.

696
00:29:37,469 --> 00:29:39,905
So, you're the one that
eats all the cookies.

697
00:29:39,938 --> 00:29:41,741
Um, how did you know?

698
00:29:42,876 --> 00:29:44,977
[Katie] I heard. [laughs]

699
00:29:47,146 --> 00:29:48,480
[Andrew] Hmm.

700
00:29:53,887 --> 00:29:55,254
Hey, Dad.

701
00:29:55,287 --> 00:29:56,321
Oh hey, pumpkin.

702
00:29:56,355 --> 00:29:57,356
How was your day?

703
00:29:57,389 --> 00:29:58,257
It was great.

704
00:29:58,290 --> 00:29:59,057
Oh, that's right,

705
00:29:59,091 --> 00:29:59,859
it was your third date.

706
00:29:59,893 --> 00:30:00,860
How'd it go?

707
00:30:00,894 --> 00:30:02,361
Dad, it's not a date.

708
00:30:02,394 --> 00:30:06,532
Alright, alright, it
wasn't a date. [laughs]

709
00:30:06,565 --> 00:30:08,934
Look, I got some dinner in
the fridge for you, alright?

710
00:30:08,967 --> 00:30:10,269
Don't be up too late,
school tomorrow.

711
00:30:10,302 --> 00:30:11,236
I won't.

712
00:30:11,270 --> 00:30:12,037
- Thanks, Dad.
- Alright, alright.

713
00:30:12,070 --> 00:30:12,938
Goodnight.

714
00:30:15,140 --> 00:30:16,910
We're gonna be okay, Abby, girl.

715
00:30:21,980 --> 00:30:24,082
[gentle music]

716
00:30:24,116 --> 00:30:26,018
So, I was thinking we
could go to Mayfields.

717
00:30:26,051 --> 00:30:27,854
I heard they have a sale, so.

718
00:30:29,756 --> 00:30:31,891
Katie, Katie, are you okay?

719
00:30:33,893 --> 00:30:34,828
Sorry, what?

720
00:30:36,763 --> 00:30:38,397
Is everything alright?

721
00:30:40,834 --> 00:30:41,801
No, not really.

722
00:30:43,937 --> 00:30:46,271
Okay, I can just pull over.

723
00:30:52,946 --> 00:30:53,813
What's going on?

724
00:30:55,280 --> 00:30:56,348
Everything, Lindsey.

725
00:30:57,951 --> 00:30:58,852
Tell me.

726
00:31:02,254 --> 00:31:03,622
My mom has cancer.

727
00:31:05,023 --> 00:31:06,024
Stage four.

728
00:31:07,894 --> 00:31:08,994
[Lindsey] What?

729
00:31:09,027 --> 00:31:12,632
I'm trying to be
strong. [sniffles]

730
00:31:12,665 --> 00:31:13,766
We just found out.

731
00:31:14,968 --> 00:31:16,970
It's bad, but she said
she's going to fight.

732
00:31:18,103 --> 00:31:19,238
I'm so sorry.
[Katie sobbing]

733
00:31:19,271 --> 00:31:20,572
God, I can't even...

734
00:31:20,606 --> 00:31:22,809
I don't know what to do.

735
00:31:24,009 --> 00:31:25,979
I don't want her
to see me crying.

736
00:31:26,011 --> 00:31:27,112
I'm so scared.

737
00:31:28,146 --> 00:31:29,581
Hey, hey, it's gonna be okay.

738
00:31:29,615 --> 00:31:31,951
I'm gonna be here for
you no matter what, okay?

739
00:31:35,922 --> 00:31:36,890
Thank you.

740
00:31:40,192 --> 00:31:41,995
How about we talk
about some happy stuff?

741
00:31:42,027 --> 00:31:43,663
Okay.

742
00:31:43,696 --> 00:31:46,900
Isn't that, what's his face
who's taking you to prom,

743
00:31:46,933 --> 00:31:47,867
that guy?

744
00:31:47,901 --> 00:31:48,935
Brett.

745
00:31:48,968 --> 00:31:52,538
Brett, the
basketball guy, yeah.

746
00:31:52,571 --> 00:31:54,473
He hasn't asked me yet,

747
00:31:54,506 --> 00:31:56,508
but I was thinking it'd be fun

748
00:31:56,542 --> 00:31:59,344
if just a bunch of
us went together.

749
00:31:59,378 --> 00:32:00,546
Yeah, gonna be fine.

750
00:32:00,579 --> 00:32:02,214
We can get a limo,
ride in style.

751
00:32:05,752 --> 00:32:07,020
Love you, girl.

752
00:32:07,052 --> 00:32:08,053
It's gonna be okay.

753
00:32:11,056 --> 00:32:13,927
[Katie sniffling]

754
00:32:17,462 --> 00:32:18,765
[gentle music]

755
00:32:18,798 --> 00:32:20,733
So, you excited
for prom tonight?

756
00:32:20,767 --> 00:32:21,567
Yeah.

757
00:32:22,936 --> 00:32:23,903
Do you think it's weird,

758
00:32:23,937 --> 00:32:25,137
Lindsey and I decided
not to go with any boys,

759
00:32:25,170 --> 00:32:27,539
and just go with
our girlfriends?

760
00:32:27,573 --> 00:32:29,042
Oh, yeah, it's so weird, Kat,

761
00:32:30,643 --> 00:32:32,578
but better for your dad and I.

762
00:32:32,611 --> 00:32:34,013
Now, we don't have to do

763
00:32:34,047 --> 00:32:37,549
that whole crazy father
parent thing that dads do.

764
00:32:39,217 --> 00:32:42,588
[doorbell ringing]

765
00:32:42,621 --> 00:32:44,523
Here's the lovely
Miss Lindsey.

766
00:32:44,556 --> 00:32:45,324
[Lindsey] Hi!

767
00:32:46,258 --> 00:32:47,426
I'll be right back.

768
00:32:47,459 --> 00:32:49,227
[Lindsey] Hello,
Sara, how are you doing?

769
00:32:49,261 --> 00:32:50,863
I'm fighting hard.

770
00:32:50,897 --> 00:32:52,097
It's good to see you.

771
00:32:52,130 --> 00:32:54,033
[Lindsey] It's
good to see you too.

772
00:32:54,067 --> 00:32:55,233
Why don't we go get ready?

773
00:32:55,267 --> 00:32:56,803
[Lindsey] Okay, bye.

774
00:32:56,836 --> 00:32:58,203
You girls have fun.

775
00:32:58,236 --> 00:32:59,237
[Katie] Thank you, Mom.

776
00:33:04,142 --> 00:33:06,946
[Lindsey] Sorry, I
left my makeup bag.

777
00:33:06,980 --> 00:33:09,082
Actually, I'm
glad you're here.

778
00:33:09,114 --> 00:33:10,683
Can you sit with
me for a minute?

779
00:33:12,150 --> 00:33:13,086
Yeah, of course.

780
00:33:13,118 --> 00:33:14,087
What's wrong?

781
00:33:14,119 --> 00:33:16,121
I need your help, Lindsey.

782
00:33:16,154 --> 00:33:17,790
I don't have long.

783
00:33:19,025 --> 00:33:21,027
I'm struggling with it.

784
00:33:22,494 --> 00:33:26,131
And I know that Katie is not
gonna do well when I'm gone.

785
00:33:28,101 --> 00:33:29,769
I wanna do something for her,

786
00:33:30,770 --> 00:33:32,105
that'll bring her comfort

787
00:33:33,305 --> 00:33:35,108
you know, during important
times in her life.

788
00:33:36,643 --> 00:33:39,344
Will you help me make a
video message for her?

789
00:33:41,114 --> 00:33:42,314
Yeah.

790
00:33:42,347 --> 00:33:44,117
Yeah, of course.

791
00:33:44,149 --> 00:33:46,351
And don't tell her.

792
00:33:48,121 --> 00:33:49,154
I'll entrust them to you,

793
00:33:50,522 --> 00:33:52,792
and you just make
sure she gets them

794
00:33:52,825 --> 00:33:55,128
when the time's right, okay?

795
00:33:57,162 --> 00:33:58,665
Okay.

796
00:33:58,698 --> 00:33:59,832
Okay.

797
00:33:59,866 --> 00:34:00,933
You go on, get ready.

798
00:34:02,135 --> 00:34:05,504
I'll contact you to set
up a day and time soon.

799
00:34:07,140 --> 00:34:08,141
I'll see you.

800
00:34:09,008 --> 00:34:09,809
Bye.

801
00:34:14,579 --> 00:34:15,882
- Tom?
- Yes, dear.

802
00:34:15,915 --> 00:34:17,684
Can you bring me
my Bible, please?

803
00:34:20,585 --> 00:34:22,121
Anything for you, my love.

804
00:34:25,223 --> 00:34:26,491
You mind if I read with you?

805
00:34:26,525 --> 00:34:27,325
No.

806
00:34:34,399 --> 00:34:37,402
[melancholic music]

807
00:34:38,705 --> 00:34:40,305
Oh, oh, thank you.

808
00:34:42,374 --> 00:34:44,644
Katie sure did look
beautiful for the prom tonight,

809
00:34:44,677 --> 00:34:45,444
didn't she?

810
00:34:45,477 --> 00:34:46,244
Oh, she did.

811
00:34:50,482 --> 00:34:51,718
There you go.

812
00:34:53,886 --> 00:34:56,789
[Sara groaning]

813
00:34:56,823 --> 00:34:58,024
Thank you, honey.

814
00:34:58,057 --> 00:34:59,892
Huh, for what?

815
00:34:59,926 --> 00:35:01,293
You know.

816
00:35:01,326 --> 00:35:02,527
What, for loving you?

817
00:35:04,197 --> 00:35:05,564
I love you, Tom.

818
00:35:06,699 --> 00:35:10,036
And I know you're going
to do the right thing,

819
00:35:10,069 --> 00:35:12,337
and raise our daughter right.

820
00:35:13,238 --> 00:35:15,141
I'm not giving
up on you, Sara.

821
00:35:16,274 --> 00:35:21,279
I know.

822
00:35:37,163 --> 00:35:38,631
Thank you for this, Lindsey.

823
00:35:38,664 --> 00:35:39,832
You're welcome, Sara.

824
00:35:41,000 --> 00:35:43,169
I know how much this
is gonna mean to Katie.

825
00:35:44,402 --> 00:35:45,270
Right.

826
00:35:46,839 --> 00:35:48,273
It means everything to me too.

827
00:35:50,475 --> 00:35:52,979
I don't have much
I can leave her,

828
00:35:54,513 --> 00:35:58,885
but reminders of how
proud I am of her,

829
00:36:00,787 --> 00:36:01,788
how much I love her,

830
00:36:03,790 --> 00:36:05,758
bring me some peace.

831
00:36:05,792 --> 00:36:07,592
She's gonna be here
in about 30 minutes,

832
00:36:07,627 --> 00:36:10,263
so we should get started.

833
00:36:12,297 --> 00:36:15,101
I'm just gonna put
some lipstick on.

834
00:36:15,134 --> 00:36:16,235
Of course,

835
00:36:24,677 --> 00:36:25,778
How does that look?

836
00:36:26,779 --> 00:36:28,281
You look beautiful.

837
00:36:32,317 --> 00:36:34,787
Okay, I'm ready when you are.

838
00:36:38,791 --> 00:36:42,094
Katie, when you
receive this message,

839
00:36:44,263 --> 00:36:49,068
I'll be with God and our
savior, Jesus Christ,

840
00:36:49,101 --> 00:36:51,536
in heaven and free of pain.

841
00:36:55,507 --> 00:36:59,212
I will always be watching
over you in spirit.

842
00:37:02,281 --> 00:37:04,283
And today is such a special day.

843
00:37:05,617 --> 00:37:09,322
You're graduating from
high school with honors,

844
00:37:11,356 --> 00:37:13,358
and I'm so proud of you.

845
00:37:15,560 --> 00:37:17,495
I want you to enjoy it,

846
00:37:21,334 --> 00:37:25,370
and take tons of pictures with
your friends and your dad.

847
00:37:26,939 --> 00:37:28,373
And enjoy that moment,

848
00:37:29,342 --> 00:37:30,575
when you move your tassel,

849
00:37:32,377 --> 00:37:33,913
and throw your hat in the air.

850
00:37:37,283 --> 00:37:41,386
Going to UF is going
to be amazing for you,

851
00:37:44,323 --> 00:37:46,025
and I hope that you have

852
00:37:46,058 --> 00:37:49,262
a memorable college
experience, honey.

853
00:37:51,429 --> 00:37:56,434
Katie, please try and
go to church regularly.

854
00:37:58,403 --> 00:38:01,406
Read your Bible and pray.

855
00:38:04,409 --> 00:38:05,945
I've left my Bible for you,

856
00:38:09,115 --> 00:38:13,551
and I've had Pastor Mark notate
all my favorite Bible verses

857
00:38:14,820 --> 00:38:16,122
for you to reference,

858
00:38:19,025 --> 00:38:20,126
and give you strength.

859
00:38:22,460 --> 00:38:25,197
I will always be with you.

860
00:38:29,467 --> 00:38:30,703
I love you, Katie.

861
00:38:33,205 --> 00:38:35,875
[Sara sniffling]

862
00:38:42,114 --> 00:38:43,416
Okay, I got it.

863
00:38:46,618 --> 00:38:49,088
Lindsey, I have
one more favor.

864
00:38:50,488 --> 00:38:51,424
Yeah.

865
00:38:53,993 --> 00:38:54,794
Anything.

866
00:38:56,963 --> 00:38:58,898
I got a graduation
card for Katie.

867
00:39:02,134 --> 00:39:05,271
Can you make sure she gets
it when she graduates?

868
00:39:08,606 --> 00:39:10,443
Yeah, of course.

869
00:39:11,811 --> 00:39:16,449
But you'll be able to
give it to her, right?

870
00:39:20,485 --> 00:39:21,454
Appreciate it.

871
00:39:22,955 --> 00:39:25,958
[Lindsey sniffling]

872
00:39:30,528 --> 00:39:32,264
Thank you so much
for sharing, Rick,

873
00:39:32,298 --> 00:39:34,200
and let's put that
in your memory book.

874
00:39:35,368 --> 00:39:36,469
Hello, Lindsey.

875
00:39:38,471 --> 00:39:39,872
- Hi.
- Hey, Lindsey.

876
00:39:39,905 --> 00:39:41,440
I'm sorry I'm late.
[gentle music]

877
00:39:41,474 --> 00:39:43,242
I was helping my friend's
mom with something.

878
00:39:43,275 --> 00:39:44,143
No, that's okay.

879
00:39:44,176 --> 00:39:45,177
Sometimes we have things to do.

880
00:39:45,211 --> 00:39:46,445
Don't worry about it.

881
00:39:46,479 --> 00:39:48,180
Well, it wouldn't be
the same without you.

882
00:39:49,448 --> 00:39:51,751
I'm having a hard
time with this one.

883
00:39:51,784 --> 00:39:52,617
Why?

884
00:39:54,220 --> 00:39:57,957
It's my best friend's
mom, she's dying,

885
00:39:57,990 --> 00:40:00,760
and I'm trying to do
something special for Katie

886
00:40:00,793 --> 00:40:03,496
so she can have something
after she's gone.

887
00:40:03,528 --> 00:40:06,132
Well, that's very
sweet of you to help her.

888
00:40:06,165 --> 00:40:07,233
But are you okay?

889
00:40:08,401 --> 00:40:12,738
I am, but I can't stop
thinking about my mom.

890
00:40:14,306 --> 00:40:16,742
Sometimes, it's just like
I lost her all over again.

891
00:40:19,045 --> 00:40:21,213
Well, I'm sure what
you're doing to help Katie

892
00:40:21,247 --> 00:40:22,580
will bring her great comfort.

893
00:40:24,549 --> 00:40:26,986
Well, I'm helping her mom
make a video message for her,

894
00:40:27,019 --> 00:40:28,387
and I still have to edit it

895
00:40:28,421 --> 00:40:29,688
with some of her mom's
favorite pictures at the end.

896
00:40:29,722 --> 00:40:33,426
But, I don't know.

897
00:40:33,459 --> 00:40:34,260
I like that.

898
00:40:35,661 --> 00:40:37,430
I'd love to see
my brother again.

899
00:40:38,431 --> 00:40:39,932
Or my baby.

900
00:40:39,965 --> 00:40:40,766
Or my husband.

901
00:40:41,934 --> 00:40:42,735
My father.

902
00:40:43,903 --> 00:40:44,703
My mom.

903
00:40:46,604 --> 00:40:48,474
You know, I think
we all have someone

904
00:40:48,507 --> 00:40:50,509
whose voice we'd
love to hear again.

905
00:40:51,911 --> 00:40:54,180
I think it's very sweet of
you to help your friend.

906
00:40:54,213 --> 00:40:56,749
And you know, you could always
invite Katie here, you know?

907
00:40:56,782 --> 00:40:59,351
She doesn't have to wait
until her mother passes

908
00:40:59,385 --> 00:41:00,753
to get support.

909
00:41:00,786 --> 00:41:02,088
I don't know.

910
00:41:02,121 --> 00:41:03,556
She's not ready to deal
with her mom dying yet.

911
00:41:05,558 --> 00:41:07,293
And Sara's still fighting.

912
00:41:08,127 --> 00:41:09,195
Maybe she'll make it.

913
00:41:10,029 --> 00:41:10,796
It's true.

914
00:41:10,830 --> 00:41:11,630
We'll be praying.

915
00:41:12,965 --> 00:41:13,799
Thanks.

916
00:41:15,568 --> 00:41:16,435
Ava would you like
[phone ringing]

917
00:41:16,469 --> 00:41:17,236
to continue with your story?

918
00:41:17,269 --> 00:41:18,170
[Ava] Alright.

919
00:41:18,204 --> 00:41:19,138
[John] Oh, why
don't you go ahead

920
00:41:19,171 --> 00:41:20,005
and check that?

921
00:41:20,039 --> 00:41:20,773
It doesn't happen often,

922
00:41:20,806 --> 00:41:22,208
it might be important.

923
00:41:22,241 --> 00:41:22,975
I'm so sorry.

924
00:41:23,008 --> 00:41:24,844
I have to go.

925
00:41:24,877 --> 00:41:25,644
No worries.

926
00:41:33,452 --> 00:41:35,888
Where are you?

927
00:41:37,723 --> 00:41:40,726
[Daniel sighs]

928
00:41:40,759 --> 00:41:41,560
Dad, what happened?

929
00:41:41,594 --> 00:41:42,528
You're scaring me.

930
00:41:47,833 --> 00:41:49,602
Katie's mom passed away.

931
00:41:49,635 --> 00:41:50,703
Oh, I need to go see her.

932
00:41:50,736 --> 00:41:51,937
No, no, no, no, no,
listen, you can't.

933
00:41:51,971 --> 00:41:53,539
They're at the hospital.

934
00:41:53,572 --> 00:41:55,040
You're not gonna be able
to see them until tomorrow.

935
00:41:55,074 --> 00:41:55,841
I'm sorry.

936
00:41:57,510 --> 00:42:00,613
We finished just in time.
[melancholic music]

937
00:42:00,646 --> 00:42:03,315
What, what did you, what?

938
00:42:03,349 --> 00:42:04,583
What?

939
00:42:04,617 --> 00:42:06,485
Her mom and I, we made
this video for Katie

940
00:42:06,519 --> 00:42:07,686
for her graduation.

941
00:42:09,555 --> 00:42:10,656
It's like, she knew.

942
00:42:12,658 --> 00:42:14,793
That's gonna mean
the world to her.

943
00:42:14,827 --> 00:42:17,563
It's like losing
Mom all over again.

944
00:42:17,596 --> 00:42:18,330
Yeah, I know.

945
00:42:18,364 --> 00:42:19,431
That's why I wanted to-

946
00:42:19,465 --> 00:42:20,766
- Hey, Dad, I really, I
really need to be alone.

947
00:42:20,799 --> 00:42:22,701
No, no, no just wait.

948
00:42:24,370 --> 00:42:26,906
[Daniel sighs]

949
00:42:41,487 --> 00:42:42,855
This is so beautiful, Mom.

950
00:42:44,658 --> 00:42:46,660
I wonder what you
would have said to me.

951
00:42:48,394 --> 00:42:49,895
But I know this will help Katie.

952
00:42:51,665 --> 00:42:52,632
I just know.

953
00:43:21,227 --> 00:43:24,029
I think Mom would
have liked the ceremony.

954
00:43:24,063 --> 00:43:25,731
Yeah, I think so too.

955
00:43:31,705 --> 00:43:33,038
Does the pain ever go away?

956
00:43:34,740 --> 00:43:36,208
Honestly?

957
00:43:36,242 --> 00:43:38,210
It does and it doesn't.

958
00:43:41,213 --> 00:43:42,548
We'll never stop missing them.

959
00:43:44,383 --> 00:43:45,719
I don't know how you did it.

960
00:43:46,720 --> 00:43:47,519
It's so hard.

961
00:43:50,289 --> 00:43:53,025
Time, remember
the good things.

962
00:43:53,959 --> 00:43:54,860
[air whooshing]

963
00:43:54,893 --> 00:43:56,895
Mom, do you think I can do it?

964
00:43:56,929 --> 00:43:57,763
[Abby] You can do it, Lindsey.

965
00:43:57,796 --> 00:43:58,864
I believe in you.

966
00:44:00,466 --> 00:44:03,435
[water splashing]

967
00:44:03,469 --> 00:44:04,903
[air whooshing]

968
00:44:04,937 --> 00:44:07,006
[Lindsey] I guess
that sometimes helps.

969
00:44:07,973 --> 00:44:09,643
We graduate in one month.

970
00:44:11,745 --> 00:44:13,680
She wanted to be
here so bad for that.

971
00:44:13,713 --> 00:44:15,214
Just one more month.

972
00:44:17,751 --> 00:44:20,486
I know this probably
won't mean much right now,

973
00:44:23,255 --> 00:44:25,491
but I truly believe
that she's here with us.

974
00:44:27,661 --> 00:44:28,762
She's with God now.

975
00:44:31,130 --> 00:44:32,064
[gentle music]

976
00:44:32,097 --> 00:44:33,098
It's not the same.

977
00:44:39,773 --> 00:44:40,539
Hey.

978
00:44:47,479 --> 00:44:48,782
Just, I wonder why
she's not here yet.

979
00:44:48,814 --> 00:44:50,115
She's never late.

980
00:44:50,149 --> 00:44:51,350
I don't know.

981
00:44:51,383 --> 00:44:53,218
Maybe call her?

982
00:44:53,252 --> 00:44:54,620
I don't know.

983
00:44:54,654 --> 00:44:55,821
I have a really bad
feeling about this,

984
00:44:55,854 --> 00:44:57,589
like she's not okay.

985
00:44:57,623 --> 00:44:58,991
I'm sure she's alright.

986
00:44:59,024 --> 00:45:00,592
Just call her.

987
00:45:00,627 --> 00:45:01,527
Okay, well.

988
00:45:02,629 --> 00:45:03,797
[phone buzzing]

989
00:45:03,829 --> 00:45:05,164
Oh, I bet that's her now.

990
00:45:11,470 --> 00:45:13,005
Everything okay?

991
00:45:13,038 --> 00:45:14,139
No, it's not.

992
00:45:14,173 --> 00:45:15,809
Katie's not okay.

993
00:45:15,841 --> 00:45:16,942
[Andrew] What happened?

994
00:45:16,975 --> 00:45:18,077
She said she's not coming.

995
00:45:18,110 --> 00:45:19,912
She said she can't stop crying.

996
00:45:20,979 --> 00:45:22,816
It's gonna be alright.

997
00:45:22,881 --> 00:45:24,651
[Lindsey] What should I do?

998
00:45:24,684 --> 00:45:26,151
What can you do?

999
00:45:26,185 --> 00:45:28,887
I mean, I can go give her
the message from her mom.

1000
00:45:30,022 --> 00:45:31,590
I know it's supposed to
be for the graduation,

1001
00:45:31,623 --> 00:45:34,694
but I think she needs it now.

1002
00:45:34,728 --> 00:45:35,829
You sure?

1003
00:45:35,861 --> 00:45:37,029
I mean, it is your party.

1004
00:45:38,597 --> 00:45:40,165
You sure?

1005
00:45:40,199 --> 00:45:42,000
I don't know.

1006
00:45:42,034 --> 00:45:43,969
Why do bad things
happen to good people?

1007
00:45:44,002 --> 00:45:45,371
I just don't understand.

1008
00:45:45,404 --> 00:45:46,972
Hey, hey, hey, you know what?

1009
00:45:47,005 --> 00:45:49,375
You know what, listen,

1010
00:45:49,408 --> 00:45:50,876
I'll finish these
decorations up,

1011
00:45:50,909 --> 00:45:52,277
and you go see Katie.

1012
00:45:52,311 --> 00:45:53,879
Deliver that message to her.

1013
00:45:53,912 --> 00:45:54,814
Are you sure?

1014
00:45:54,848 --> 00:45:55,815
I'm sure, alright.

1015
00:45:55,849 --> 00:45:57,616
Parties come and go,

1016
00:45:57,650 --> 00:45:59,151
but best friends are forever.

1017
00:45:59,184 --> 00:46:00,185
Thank you.

1018
00:46:01,086 --> 00:46:04,089
[Lindsey sniffling]

1019
00:46:14,933 --> 00:46:17,837
[hopeful music]

1020
00:46:17,871 --> 00:46:18,838
Katie.

1021
00:46:20,072 --> 00:46:21,473
Lindsey.

1022
00:46:21,507 --> 00:46:23,275
Hey, it's gonna be okay.

1023
00:46:24,910 --> 00:46:25,779
I'm not so sure.

1024
00:46:28,313 --> 00:46:30,416
I'm not ready to
be without my mom.

1025
00:46:30,449 --> 00:46:32,886
I know, I know,
but she's with you.

1026
00:46:32,918 --> 00:46:33,952
How would you know?

1027
00:46:34,953 --> 00:46:36,422
I have something for you?

1028
00:46:37,923 --> 00:46:39,925
I was supposed to give it
to you after graduation,

1029
00:46:39,958 --> 00:46:41,059
but I don't think
your mom would mind

1030
00:46:41,093 --> 00:46:41,994
if I gave it to you now.

1031
00:46:42,027 --> 00:46:43,095
What do you mean, my mom?

1032
00:46:43,128 --> 00:46:44,864
It's from your mom.

1033
00:46:44,898 --> 00:46:46,031
She made it for you.

1034
00:46:46,064 --> 00:46:47,032
What is this about?

1035
00:46:47,065 --> 00:46:48,100
What is this?

1036
00:46:48,133 --> 00:46:48,934
Just trust me.

1037
00:46:52,104 --> 00:46:53,272
Watch it.

1038
00:46:53,305 --> 00:46:57,309
Katie, when you
receive this message,

1039
00:46:58,944 --> 00:47:03,783
I'll be with God and our
savior, Jesus Christ,

1040
00:47:03,817 --> 00:47:06,552
in heaven and free of pain.

1041
00:47:10,155 --> 00:47:13,927
I will always be watching
over you in spirit.

1042
00:47:17,129 --> 00:47:19,097
Today is such a special day.

1043
00:47:20,532 --> 00:47:23,602
You're graduating from
high school with honors,

1044
00:47:26,371 --> 00:47:28,006
and I'm so proud of you.

1045
00:47:31,009 --> 00:47:32,812
I want you to enjoy it.

1046
00:47:32,846 --> 00:47:33,947
I'm sorry, Katie.

1047
00:47:33,979 --> 00:47:35,949
I didn't mean to make
you cry like this.

1048
00:47:36,014 --> 00:47:37,282
- Take tons of pictures
- No.

1049
00:47:37,316 --> 00:47:38,984
[Sara] with your
friends and your dad.

1050
00:47:39,017 --> 00:47:40,619
No, it's just so beautiful.

1051
00:47:41,688 --> 00:47:43,555
And enjoy that moment.
[hopeful music]

1052
00:47:43,589 --> 00:47:44,824
I miss her so much.

1053
00:47:44,858 --> 00:47:45,692
[Sara] When you
move your tassel.

1054
00:47:45,725 --> 00:47:46,926
Thank you.

1055
00:47:46,960 --> 00:47:47,827
- Yeah.
- And throw your hat

1056
00:47:47,861 --> 00:47:49,461
in the air.

1057
00:47:49,495 --> 00:47:51,330
Kat, you should come to
group with me sometime.

1058
00:47:51,363 --> 00:47:52,130
Maybe.

1059
00:47:52,164 --> 00:47:53,198
Going to you UF,

1060
00:47:54,199 --> 00:47:55,367
- I'll just take it
- is going to be

1061
00:47:55,400 --> 00:47:56,602
- one day at a time.
- amazing for you.

1062
00:47:56,636 --> 00:47:57,436
Okay.

1063
00:47:57,469 --> 00:47:58,237
[Sara] Katie.

1064
00:47:58,270 --> 00:48:00,907
Oh, open your card.

1065
00:48:00,940 --> 00:48:03,877
