00:57:24,537 --> 00:57:25,838
- Yeah.
- You know,

1322
00:57:25,871 --> 00:57:29,208
it was only the beginning
before this happened.

1323
00:57:29,241 --> 00:57:30,509
Yeah, yeah, I got you.

1324
00:57:30,543 --> 00:57:32,211
What's his name?

1325
00:57:32,244 --> 00:57:33,712
His name is Jake.

1326
00:57:33,746 --> 00:57:36,182
Yeah, yeah, I'll
deliver it myself.

1327
00:57:36,215 --> 00:57:37,516
Oh, thank you, man, thank you.

1328
00:57:37,550 --> 00:57:40,186
Oh, one more thing?

1329
00:57:40,219 --> 00:57:41,153
Yeah, what is it?

1330
00:57:42,721 --> 00:57:44,090
50, actually.

1331
00:57:44,123 --> 00:57:45,891
[Andrew] What do you mean?

1332
00:57:45,925 --> 00:57:47,526
It's, it's for my dad.

1333
00:57:47,560 --> 00:57:49,762
[gentle music]

1334
00:57:49,795 --> 00:57:51,964
Yeah, there's a few notes
and whatnot for my mom,

1335
00:57:51,997 --> 00:57:54,467
but his birthday is next month.

1336
00:57:58,904 --> 00:58:00,306
[Lindsey] That's so sweet.

1337
00:58:01,640 --> 00:58:02,741
Thanks.

1338
00:58:02,775 --> 00:58:05,311
Hopefully he can get
some laughs out of it.

1339
00:58:06,645 --> 00:58:08,047
You know, we are pretty close,

1340
00:58:08,080 --> 00:58:11,016
and he hasn't been
taking this very well.

1341
00:58:11,050 --> 00:58:13,719
[Brian coughing]

1342
00:58:16,922 --> 00:58:19,624
Well, Brian, we're
actually just about ready.

1343
00:58:19,658 --> 00:58:20,626
How you doing?

1344
00:58:21,627 --> 00:58:23,095
Oh, I've been better,

1345
00:58:23,129 --> 00:58:24,396
but I'm gonna say,

1346
00:58:24,430 --> 00:58:26,765
this is, this is great.

1347
00:58:28,567 --> 00:58:31,203
I'm just thankful I
could even do this.

1348
00:58:31,237 --> 00:58:33,539
Hopefully it brings
me some peace.

1349
00:58:33,572 --> 00:58:35,341
Well, before we
all start crying,

1350
00:58:36,308 --> 00:58:37,877
Brian, you ready?

1351
00:58:39,178 --> 00:58:43,015
[Brian] [sighs]
Just tell me when.

1352
00:58:43,048 --> 00:58:45,584
[Ricky] Whenever you're
ready, the camera's rolling.

1353
00:58:45,618 --> 00:58:46,452
Alright.

1354
00:58:48,587 --> 00:58:53,526
So, Dad, I hear you're
turning 50 next month, man.

1355
00:58:54,628 --> 00:58:56,228
[Brian chuckles]

1356
00:58:56,262 --> 00:58:57,596
Oh, geez.

1357
00:58:57,631 --> 00:58:59,633
Looks like you're heading
over that hill, huh?

1358
00:59:01,200 --> 00:59:03,637
Look, I just, I just wanted
to wish you happy birthday.

1359
00:59:04,904 --> 00:59:09,308
Mom, give the old man a
hug from me, yeah? [laughs]

1360
00:59:09,341 --> 00:59:12,044
[Brian coughing]

1361
00:59:13,512 --> 00:59:18,317
Look, Mom, I'm sure when
you had children, you know,

1362
00:59:20,219 --> 00:59:25,224
this wasn't exactly what you
had in mind for our future

1363
00:59:25,424 --> 00:59:26,225
or anything.

1364
00:59:28,394 --> 00:59:33,432
But I just want to
let you know, [coughs]

1365
00:59:39,171 --> 00:59:42,174
even though my
time here is short,

1366
00:59:48,247 --> 00:59:49,748
I had a wonderful life.

1367
00:59:50,983 --> 00:59:52,985
I couldn't have asked
for a better family.

1368
00:59:56,021 --> 00:59:58,190
I'm always gonna be
watching over you, kid.

1369
00:59:59,258 --> 01:00:00,593
Because God has a plan.

1370
01:00:02,962 --> 01:00:04,664
So, remember these two things,

1371
01:00:08,702 --> 01:00:09,768
keep your faith,

1372
01:00:11,604 --> 01:00:12,805
and I will always love you.

1373
01:00:17,610 --> 01:00:22,181
Thank you for giving me
such a wonderful life.

1374
01:00:38,264 --> 01:00:39,798
[gentle music]

1375
01:00:39,832 --> 01:00:41,000
He was really sweet.

1376
01:00:42,736 --> 01:00:43,502
He was.

1377
01:00:45,304 --> 01:00:47,439
It must be hard for them,

1378
01:00:47,473 --> 01:00:49,308
not having their parents
know who they are.

1379
01:00:51,143 --> 01:00:53,112
I mean, at least
they have each other.

1380
01:00:54,980 --> 01:00:56,650
Yeah.

1381
01:00:56,683 --> 01:00:58,652
Me and Josh really needed
each other when my mom died.

1382
01:00:59,785 --> 01:01:01,553
I never realized just how much.

1383
01:01:02,722 --> 01:01:05,759
No, it isn't easy
what we're doing.

1384
01:01:05,791 --> 01:01:10,796
It, you know, it doesn't make
the pain and loss go away.

1385
01:01:12,264 --> 01:01:14,466
But I hope that it makes
them feel less alone.

1386
01:01:15,434 --> 01:01:18,270
Yeah, me too.

1387
01:01:27,446 --> 01:01:29,749
I can't believe we've
already helped 50 people.

1388
01:01:29,783 --> 01:01:30,816
Yeah, I know, it's crazy.

1389
01:01:30,849 --> 01:01:32,418
We've helped a
lot of people out.

1390
01:01:32,451 --> 01:01:34,887
Like, I was thinking people,
like, wouldn't like my idea,

1391
01:01:34,920 --> 01:01:37,823
but it's helped people so
much to see their loved ones,

1392
01:01:37,856 --> 01:01:38,957
- you know?
- Yeah, yeah,

1393
01:01:38,991 --> 01:01:40,959
I mean, we're impacting
a lot of lives.

1394
01:01:40,993 --> 01:01:43,829
A lot of people are gonna be
impacted by what we're doing.

1395
01:01:43,862 --> 01:01:45,097
And there's hundreds more.

1396
01:01:45,130 --> 01:01:46,800
It can never end.

1397
01:01:46,832 --> 01:01:47,933
We could do this forever.

1398
01:01:47,966 --> 01:01:49,368
Yeah.

1399
01:01:49,401 --> 01:01:50,202
I can't.

1400
01:01:51,638 --> 01:01:52,438
[gentle music]

1401
01:01:52,471 --> 01:01:53,640
Hey Linds?

1402
01:01:53,673 --> 01:01:55,207
[Lindsey] Yeah?

1403
01:01:55,240 --> 01:01:59,111
I was thinking maybe, maybe
we can go to dinner sometime?

1404
01:01:59,144 --> 01:02:00,279
- Hang out a bit.
- That'd be fun.

1405
01:02:00,312 --> 01:02:02,816
We can invite Katie.

1406
01:02:02,848 --> 01:02:03,783
Hey.

1407
01:02:03,817 --> 01:02:04,651
Hey, Ricky.

1408
01:02:05,551 --> 01:02:06,985
- Got my camera.
- What's up?

1409
01:02:07,821 --> 01:02:09,621
Yeah, we're good.

1410
01:02:09,656 --> 01:02:12,191
Yeah, but I was
thinking more me and you,

1411
01:02:12,224 --> 01:02:13,359
more of a me and you thing.

1412
01:02:13,392 --> 01:02:14,960
Not really all of us.

1413
01:02:14,993 --> 01:02:16,696
Like a date?

1414
01:02:16,730 --> 01:02:18,263
Yeah, if you want to.

1415
01:02:18,297 --> 01:02:19,465
- No, no, yeah, of course.
- I'm not trying

1416
01:02:19,498 --> 01:02:20,232
to pressure you but-

1417
01:02:20,265 --> 01:02:22,501
- Yeah, I can call Katie later.

1418
01:02:22,534 --> 01:02:23,569
Okay, yeah.

1419
01:02:25,237 --> 01:02:26,405
You ready to?

1420
01:02:27,674 --> 01:02:28,808
Let's get out of here.

1421
01:02:28,842 --> 01:02:33,646
Mikey, Michael, by
the time you see this,

1422
01:02:35,013 --> 01:02:36,548
you'll be heading off to
college, or you better be.

1423
01:02:38,450 --> 01:02:40,452
But I'll be proud of
you no matter what.

1424
01:02:41,887 --> 01:02:43,489
[Ricky] Cut.

1425
01:02:43,522 --> 01:02:44,890
One down, two to go.

1426
01:02:46,659 --> 01:02:48,193
You're strong, man.

1427
01:02:48,227 --> 01:02:49,863
It must be hard doing
this so many times.

1428
01:02:49,895 --> 01:02:51,263
Yeah, it is.

1429
01:02:51,296 --> 01:02:53,999
But hey, maybe we'll get
lucky and we won't need them.

1430
01:02:54,032 --> 01:02:55,869
They say I got some time.

1431
01:02:55,901 --> 01:02:56,902
I'm starting chemo.

1432
01:02:58,237 --> 01:03:00,339
But I knew that when I saw this,

1433
01:03:00,372 --> 01:03:02,574
that it was a great opportunity

1434
01:03:02,608 --> 01:03:05,144
to leave something
beautiful for my family,

1435
01:03:05,177 --> 01:03:07,112
just in case.

1436
01:03:07,946 --> 01:03:09,581
Well, why this park?

1437
01:03:10,416 --> 01:03:11,283
I've always been a runner.

1438
01:03:11,316 --> 01:03:13,318
It's the only way I can unwind.

1439
01:03:14,586 --> 01:03:16,890
I bring the kids with
me on shorter runs,

1440
01:03:16,922 --> 01:03:19,558
and we always stop here,
right at this bench.

1441
01:03:20,794 --> 01:03:24,463
We just, you know, talk
and laugh and goof off.

1442
01:03:25,665 --> 01:03:27,867
That's a great reason
to pick this place.

1443
01:03:29,234 --> 01:03:31,937
[Ricky] Ready for another?

1444
01:03:31,970 --> 01:03:33,439
Ready.

1445
01:03:33,472 --> 01:03:34,573
[Ricky] Camera's rolling.

1446
01:03:35,474 --> 01:03:36,942
I just want you to know

1447
01:03:36,975 --> 01:03:40,379
that you have always amazed
me with your brilliance,

1448
01:03:40,412 --> 01:03:42,948
your ability to solve problems.

1449
01:03:42,981 --> 01:03:44,784
You are such a kind soul.

1450
01:03:46,452 --> 01:03:48,153
I did a good job with you.

1451
01:03:48,187 --> 01:03:50,088
Ah, your mom helped a little.

1452
01:03:52,124 --> 01:03:54,928
What I'm saying is I love you.

1453
01:03:56,428 --> 01:03:57,897
And as you graduate,

1454
01:03:57,931 --> 01:04:01,166
know that I am with you and
watching over you always.

1455
01:04:02,568 --> 01:04:03,770
So, say your prayers,

1456
01:04:03,803 --> 01:04:05,939
and believe that great
things can happen,

1457
01:04:07,172 --> 01:04:09,141
because they can and they do.

1458
01:04:11,577 --> 01:04:14,848
And keep me in your life
by remembering me out loud.

1459
01:04:16,482 --> 01:04:18,751
Go with your mom to church.

1460
01:04:18,785 --> 01:04:19,953
Seek comfort in God,

1461
01:04:19,985 --> 01:04:23,957
because God and I, we got you.

1462
01:04:26,726 --> 01:04:27,526
I love you, kid.

1463
01:04:28,994 --> 01:04:29,963
You did good.

1464
01:04:29,995 --> 01:04:32,632
[gentle music]

1465
01:04:47,045 --> 01:04:50,315
I can't believe how many
people we've helped so far.

1466
01:04:50,349 --> 01:04:52,518
It's a blessing
for us and for them.

1467
01:04:52,551 --> 01:04:54,954
I feel like this is
my purpose, you know,

1468
01:04:54,988 --> 01:04:56,088
to help these people.

1469
01:04:56,121 --> 01:04:56,956
I don't-
[door knocking]

1470
01:04:56,990 --> 01:04:58,691
[Rebecca] Excuse me.

1471
01:04:58,725 --> 01:05:00,960
[John] Hi, yes,
how many we help you?

1472
01:05:00,994 --> 01:05:02,695
My name's Rebecca Alton.

1473
01:05:02,729 --> 01:05:03,963
I got a call from someone

1474
01:05:03,997 --> 01:05:05,965
that my mother left
something for me here?

1475
01:05:05,999 --> 01:05:07,132
Yes, hi, Rebecca.

1476
01:05:07,165 --> 01:05:08,968
Yeah, hi, I'm Lindsey.

1477
01:05:09,002 --> 01:05:10,970
We do have something from you,

1478
01:05:11,004 --> 01:05:12,872
actually from your mother.

1479
01:05:14,306 --> 01:05:17,010
My mom passed away a few
weeks ago, so how can you?

1480
01:05:17,042 --> 01:05:18,678
Well, Rebecca, we met
your mother two months ago,

1481
01:05:18,711 --> 01:05:21,014
and she left you a message.

1482
01:05:21,046 --> 01:05:22,214
Would you like to watch it now?

1483
01:05:22,247 --> 01:05:24,017
Please, it'll
bring you comfort.

1484
01:05:24,049 --> 01:05:25,018
She loves you.

1485
01:05:26,385 --> 01:05:28,620
I'm not sure that I
understand that, but okay.

1486
01:05:33,525 --> 01:05:34,861
My darling little girl,

1487
01:05:37,062 --> 01:05:38,263
when you watch this,

1488
01:05:38,297 --> 01:05:40,365
I will have moved on
to be with the Lord,

1489
01:05:41,734 --> 01:05:43,870
but I will always be with you

1490
01:05:44,971 --> 01:05:46,438
on the journey
through this life.

1491
01:05:48,140 --> 01:05:50,643
I want you to know, I love you,

1492
01:05:51,543 --> 01:05:53,478
I'm so proud of you,

1493
01:05:53,512 --> 01:05:56,615
and you will never be alone.
[Rebecca laughing]

1494
01:05:56,649 --> 01:06:00,285
I'm always be with
you in your heart.

1495
01:06:01,486 --> 01:06:02,621
I'm watching over you.

1496
01:06:04,691 --> 01:06:06,693
I love you, Mom.

1497
01:06:06,726 --> 01:06:08,061
I love you, Rebecca.

1498
01:06:09,963 --> 01:06:12,431
[car rumbling]

1499
01:06:18,103 --> 01:06:20,707
[gentle music]

1500
01:06:34,020 --> 01:06:36,121
[Andrew] Excuse me, sir.

1501
01:06:38,156 --> 01:06:39,826
What do you want?

1502
01:06:39,859 --> 01:06:41,094
I'm sorry to bother you.

1503
01:06:41,126 --> 01:06:42,996
I'm from a Living
Legacy of Love.

1504
01:06:43,029 --> 01:06:45,197
Your son, Brian, sent me.

1505
01:06:45,230 --> 01:06:48,200
[Brian's Mom] Robert, Robert?

1506
01:06:50,135 --> 01:06:51,303
What's going on here?

1507
01:06:51,336 --> 01:06:54,306
This guy, he said
that Brian sent him.

1508
01:06:56,643 --> 01:06:57,644
Why?

1509
01:06:57,677 --> 01:06:58,978
Brian's dead, leave!

1510
01:06:59,012 --> 01:07:00,780
Jake, Jake, please.

1511
01:07:00,813 --> 01:07:02,081
Brian sent us for you.

1512
01:07:02,115 --> 01:07:03,148
Why?

1513
01:07:03,181 --> 01:07:05,417
He said you needed
a big brother figure.

1514
01:07:05,450 --> 01:07:07,053
He wanted me to teach you.

1515
01:07:07,086 --> 01:07:09,588
I don't need
anything from you.

1516
01:07:09,621 --> 01:07:11,590
Jake, please
just listen to me.

1517
01:07:12,725 --> 01:07:14,292
I understand what
you're going through.

1518
01:07:14,326 --> 01:07:15,527
I lost my brother too.

1519
01:07:16,996 --> 01:07:20,099
We just wanna share the message
that Brian left for you.

1520
01:07:20,133 --> 01:07:22,167
I can leave this here and go?

1521
01:07:22,200 --> 01:07:23,970
Come on, let's go.

1522
01:07:24,003 --> 01:07:25,004
Come inside.

1523
01:07:25,038 --> 01:07:25,838
Let's talk.

1524
01:07:29,508 --> 01:07:32,912
[gentle music]

1525
01:07:32,945 --> 01:07:34,113
I don't understand.

1526
01:07:34,147 --> 01:07:36,115
What is it that Brian did?

1527
01:07:36,149 --> 01:07:38,383
[Andrew] Here,
this is for you all.

1528
01:07:38,417 --> 01:07:39,451
What is this?

1529
01:07:40,619 --> 01:07:45,024
It's a message
from your son, Brian.

1530
01:07:45,058 --> 01:07:45,825
What does it say?

1531
01:07:45,858 --> 01:07:46,959
I can't say.

1532
01:07:46,993 --> 01:07:48,094
Just, just watch.

1533
01:07:49,194 --> 01:07:50,963
Go on.

1534
01:07:50,997 --> 01:07:53,766
Son, it's, go
ahead and hit play.

1535
01:07:55,267 --> 01:07:57,436
Looks like you're heading
over that hill, huh?

1536
01:07:57,469 --> 01:08:00,707
Look, I just, I just wanted
to wish you a happy birthday.

1537
01:08:01,974 --> 01:08:04,209
Mom, give the old man
a hug from me, yeah?

1538
01:08:08,047 --> 01:08:11,184
Even though my
time here is short,

1539
01:08:17,056 --> 01:08:21,961
I had a wonderful
life, and support,

1540
01:08:24,764 --> 01:08:27,800
and I want, I want you
to feel the same as well.

1541
01:08:30,770 --> 01:08:32,705
I hope this message
brings you comfort.

1542
01:08:36,943 --> 01:08:41,114
Even though I'd much rather
be here in my own body,

1543
01:08:45,985 --> 01:08:48,154
I'm always gonna be
watching over you, kid,

1544
01:08:49,287 --> 01:08:50,422
because God has a plan.

1545
01:08:52,992 --> 01:08:54,459
So, remember these two things,

1546
01:08:58,497 --> 01:09:02,400
keep your faith and I
will always love you.

1547
01:09:04,269 --> 01:09:05,437
Thank you for listening.

1548
01:09:06,304 --> 01:09:07,339
Jake, whenever you're ready,

1549
01:09:07,372 --> 01:09:08,540
just give me a call,

1550
01:09:08,573 --> 01:09:10,575
and I'll teach you
how to use that thing.

1551
01:09:10,609 --> 01:09:11,744
[Jake] Okay.

1552
01:09:11,778 --> 01:09:13,278
[Brian's Mom] Thank you.

1553
01:09:13,311 --> 01:09:14,279
Of course.

1554
01:09:14,312 --> 01:09:15,214
[Brian's Mom]
Thank you so much.

1555
01:09:15,248 --> 01:09:16,249
This was so beautiful.

1556
01:09:17,216 --> 01:09:18,684
You're welcome.

1557
01:09:28,828 --> 01:09:31,429
[gentle music]

1558
01:09:35,600 --> 01:09:38,403
[water splashing]

1559
01:10:00,927 --> 01:10:03,095
Seriously, don't
push me in again.

1560
01:10:03,129 --> 01:10:04,997
I'm sorry, I couldn't resist.

1561
01:10:05,031 --> 01:10:05,865
You're so bad.

1562
01:10:07,300 --> 01:10:09,902
Oh, yeah, how'd it go
with Brian's family?

1563
01:10:09,936 --> 01:10:11,304
I wish you were there,

1564
01:10:11,336 --> 01:10:12,537
but it went pretty well.

1565
01:10:13,973 --> 01:10:16,309
The mom seemed to be really
moved by the message.

1566
01:10:16,341 --> 01:10:19,212
You can, you can tell the
family's still hurt by it all.

1567
01:10:20,478 --> 01:10:22,849
But I think seeing Brian's
message brought them some hope.

1568
01:10:22,882 --> 01:10:24,317
So glad we're
doing this together.

1569
01:10:24,349 --> 01:10:25,218
It just feels right.

1570
01:10:25,251 --> 01:10:26,518
It does.

1571
01:10:26,551 --> 01:10:27,854
Yeah, me too, me too.

1572
01:10:29,387 --> 01:10:30,690
Hey, I'll give you
two seconds to swim.

1573
01:10:30,723 --> 01:10:33,358
[Andrew laughs]

1574
01:10:43,169 --> 01:10:44,469
[Josh] Dad, it's 24!

1575
01:10:44,502 --> 01:10:45,338
I knew you'd get it.

1576
01:10:45,370 --> 01:10:46,272
Very good.

1577
01:10:46,305 --> 01:10:47,472
[phone ringing]

1578
01:10:47,505 --> 01:10:48,741
What else do we have here?

1579
01:10:48,774 --> 01:10:50,575
Hello, this is Lindsey.

1580
01:10:50,609 --> 01:10:52,011
[Man] Hi, Lindsey.

1581
01:10:52,044 --> 01:10:53,212
We'd like to send
our news reporter,

1582
01:10:53,246 --> 01:10:54,213
to interview you

1583
01:10:54,247 --> 01:10:56,048
about a Legacy of Love.

1584
01:10:56,082 --> 01:10:57,415
Yes, yes, when?

1585
01:10:58,751 --> 01:11:00,720
[Man] How about
Monday at 6 p.m.?

1586
01:11:00,753 --> 01:11:03,789
Okay, I'll be
there, Monday at six.

1587
01:11:03,823 --> 01:11:04,891
Thank you so much.

1588
01:11:06,359 --> 01:11:08,327
Dad, Dad, I need to
tell you something!

1589
01:11:08,361 --> 01:11:10,997
[gentle music]

1590
01:11:16,434 --> 01:11:18,838
This message
really hit me hard.

1591
01:11:18,871 --> 01:11:20,072
So much heart.

1592
01:11:21,473 --> 01:11:24,076
Dean really did love his wife.

1593
01:11:24,110 --> 01:11:24,911
I know.

1594
01:11:27,346 --> 01:11:30,415
I'm glad he called
us to record him.

1595
01:11:30,448 --> 01:11:33,352
It doesn't get easier,
doing what we're doing,

1596
01:11:33,386 --> 01:11:34,820
making these videos,

1597
01:11:34,854 --> 01:11:38,391
but there's a genuine
comfort in knowing

1598
01:11:38,423 --> 01:11:40,693
that even a little bit
of their loved ones

1599
01:11:40,726 --> 01:11:41,593
are gonna come back to them

1600
01:11:41,627 --> 01:11:43,495
through what we're doing.

1601
01:11:43,528 --> 01:11:44,830
It's something for them

1602
01:11:44,864 --> 01:11:46,399
that will live on
through generations.

1603
01:11:46,431 --> 01:11:48,734
A living legacy of love.

1604
01:11:48,768 --> 01:11:50,036
[phone ringing]

1605
01:11:50,069 --> 01:11:51,603
So, that's where
the name comes from.

1606
01:11:51,637 --> 01:11:52,939
It all makes sense now.

1607
01:11:59,477 --> 01:12:00,512
Living Legacy of Love.

1608
01:12:00,545 --> 01:12:01,479
How can I help you?

1609
01:12:03,448 --> 01:12:05,885
Okay, yeah, we can come to you,

1610
01:12:05,918 --> 01:12:07,286
or you can come to us.

1611
01:12:09,322 --> 01:12:10,588
Okay, perfect.

1612
01:12:10,622 --> 01:12:11,757
What's the address?

1613
01:12:15,460 --> 01:12:17,630
Okay, Wednesday at six.

1614
01:12:20,333 --> 01:12:21,466
We'll be there.

1615
01:12:21,499 --> 01:12:22,500
Thank you.

1616
01:12:25,537 --> 01:12:28,140
Hey, you know what'd be nice?

1617
01:12:29,775 --> 01:12:31,344
If we invited everyone
we gave the videos to,

1618
01:12:31,377 --> 01:12:32,577
to come to group.

1619
01:12:34,780 --> 01:12:35,715
[Andrew] We could do that.

1620
01:12:35,748 --> 01:12:36,916
Yeah, that's a great idea.

1621
01:12:36,949 --> 01:12:38,417
We can prepare a
special invitation,

1622
01:12:38,451 --> 01:12:40,686
and bring it with the
messages when we deliver them.

1623
01:12:42,655 --> 01:12:43,555
I love it.

1624
01:12:47,893 --> 01:12:49,362
Here they come, let's go.

1625
01:12:50,196 --> 01:12:51,430
Fantastic, okay we'll do that.

1626
01:12:51,464 --> 01:12:53,132
Yeah.

1627
01:12:53,165 --> 01:12:54,566
[Interviewer] Are you the
Living Legacy of Love group?

1628
01:12:54,599 --> 01:12:56,168
Yeah.

1629
01:12:56,202 --> 01:12:59,205
Lindsey, the Living Legacy
of Love was your brain child.

1630
01:12:59,238 --> 01:13:01,474
Now, that you've helped
over a hundred people,

1631
01:13:01,506 --> 01:13:02,475
how do you feel?

1632
01:13:03,376 --> 01:13:05,111
Well, I'm at peace with it,

1633
01:13:05,144 --> 01:13:07,780
but there are hundreds
more and it will never end.

1634
01:13:07,813 --> 01:13:10,349
As long as we can keep bringing
love and peace to people,

1635
01:13:10,383 --> 01:13:13,686
then the Living Legacy of
Love will have a place.

1636
01:13:13,719 --> 01:13:15,121
It's never ending.

1637
01:13:15,154 --> 01:13:16,588
That's beautiful.

1638
01:13:16,621 --> 01:13:20,525
Lindsey, how was the name
Living Legacy of Love chosen?

1639
01:13:20,558 --> 01:13:22,495
Was there something
that inspired you?

1640
01:13:22,527 --> 01:13:23,496
Yeah.

1641
01:13:23,528 --> 01:13:24,830
Well, our loved ones are alive

1642
01:13:24,864 --> 01:13:26,265
when they record their message.

1643
01:13:26,298 --> 01:13:28,300
And their message
is a gift of love,

1644
01:13:28,334 --> 01:13:30,503
and it's a legacy
they leave for us.

1645
01:13:31,504 --> 01:13:32,905
I mean, it's priceless,

1646
01:13:32,938 --> 01:13:35,875
worth more than any material
thing could ever be.

1647
01:13:35,908 --> 01:13:37,777
It can be shared with the
loved ones left behind,

1648
01:13:37,810 --> 01:13:40,079
and even with future
family members.

1649
01:13:40,112 --> 01:13:41,981
It's a living legacy of love,

1650
01:13:42,014 --> 01:13:44,517
as it brings them back to us,

1651
01:13:44,549 --> 01:13:46,519
even if it's just for a
few moments at a time.

1652
01:13:46,584 --> 01:13:48,854
Yeah, the name just felt right.

1653
01:13:48,888 --> 01:13:49,889
I can see that.

1654
01:13:49,922 --> 01:13:51,290
It's so powerful to know

1655
01:13:51,323 --> 01:13:53,292
that when someone's
hurting so much,

1656
01:13:53,325 --> 01:13:55,294
that they can be touched
by a loved one's message.

1657
01:13:55,327 --> 01:13:58,531
What would you want us to take
away from your experiences

1658
01:13:58,563 --> 01:14:00,733
and path of giving that?

1659
01:14:00,766 --> 01:14:02,535
When my mom died,
I was so lost.

1660
01:14:02,567 --> 01:14:05,638
I didn't think my life
could have a purpose,

1661
01:14:05,671 --> 01:14:08,507
or a direction
without her in it.

1662
01:14:08,541 --> 01:14:11,010
But slowly I realized that
we all have a purpose,

1663
01:14:11,043 --> 01:14:13,012
and we're never alone.

1664
01:14:13,045 --> 01:14:14,747
God is with us always.

1665
01:14:14,780 --> 01:14:16,549
Our loved ones are
always with us.

1666
01:14:16,581 --> 01:14:18,084
And I really want people to know

1667
01:14:18,117 --> 01:14:20,753
that even though their
loved one has crossed over,

1668
01:14:20,786 --> 01:14:22,755
they're always with you,

1669
01:14:22,788 --> 01:14:24,356
and that love never dies.

1670
01:14:25,558 --> 01:14:27,259
I think she said
it perfectly, folks.

1671
01:14:27,293 --> 01:14:30,062
If you'd like to learn more
about Living Legacy of Love,

1672
01:14:30,096 --> 01:14:32,932
go to our website and you
can find their information

1673
01:14:32,965 --> 01:14:36,068
and their links.
[gentle music]

1674
01:14:36,102 --> 01:14:37,870
Alright, thank you so much.

1675
01:14:51,750 --> 01:14:53,219
Dad?

1676
01:14:53,252 --> 01:14:54,019
Yeah.

1677
01:14:55,287 --> 01:14:56,522
Don't you think
Grandpa's dementia

1678
01:14:56,555 --> 01:14:58,791
is getting kind of bad?

1679
01:14:58,824 --> 01:15:00,459
I mean...

1680
01:15:00,493 --> 01:15:03,529
Yeah, look, you know how
Grandma's in the hospital

1681
01:15:03,562 --> 01:15:04,363
for hip surgery,

1682
01:15:06,398 --> 01:15:11,403
well when she's not around, his
memory begins to fade and...

1683
01:15:11,937 --> 01:15:13,572
Yeah.

1684
01:15:13,606 --> 01:15:16,609
I don't know, maybe we
could play a video of her,

1685
01:15:16,642 --> 01:15:18,644
see if he remembers?

1686
01:15:18,677 --> 01:15:19,612
Yeah, do you have one?

1687
01:15:19,645 --> 01:15:20,913
Yeah, I have multiple.

1688
01:15:22,314 --> 01:15:23,415
[Daniel laughs]
We could play that one?

1689
01:15:23,449 --> 01:15:25,151
That was a good day.

1690
01:15:25,184 --> 01:15:26,352
Give it a shot.

1691
01:15:26,385 --> 01:15:27,153
Right.

1692
01:15:27,186 --> 01:15:28,420
Hey, Grandpa.

1693
01:15:28,454 --> 01:15:29,221
Hey, Pop.

1694
01:15:29,255 --> 01:15:30,055
Hey, we-

1695
01:15:30,089 --> 01:15:30,956
- Pop, Pop.

1696
01:15:30,990 --> 01:15:32,925
We have a video of Grandma.

1697
01:15:32,958 --> 01:15:34,193
[Josh] Oh, let me see.

1698
01:15:35,394 --> 01:15:36,162
You remember Grandma?

1699
01:15:36,195 --> 01:15:37,096
Grandma?

1700
01:15:37,129 --> 01:15:38,097
[Grandma] Okay, open it.

1701
01:15:38,130 --> 01:15:39,265
Where is she?

1702
01:15:39,298 --> 01:15:40,599
- Are you ready?
- She's in the hospital.

1703
01:15:40,634 --> 01:15:42,601
She's in the hospital
for her hip surgery.

1704
01:15:42,636 --> 01:15:45,604
[Grandma speaking faintly]

1705
01:15:45,639 --> 01:15:48,274
Hey, look, it's her.

1706
01:15:48,307 --> 01:15:49,441
- Really?
- Really.

1707
01:15:49,475 --> 01:15:51,744
Really?
[family laughing]

1708
01:15:51,777 --> 01:15:54,648
You know I love
wine and chocolate.

1709
01:15:54,680 --> 01:15:56,615
She is so beautiful.

1710
01:15:56,650 --> 01:15:57,616
I miss her.

1711
01:15:58,617 --> 01:16:00,686
She's, look at her.

1712
01:16:00,719 --> 01:16:01,954
Oh, well, what a beautiful,

1713
01:16:01,987 --> 01:16:03,522
her smile just radiates.

1714
01:16:03,556 --> 01:16:05,191
- Aw.
- I love her, oh.

1715
01:16:05,224 --> 01:16:06,325
Oh, look at that.

1716
01:16:06,358 --> 01:16:07,627
Oh my goodness, that's...

1717
01:16:07,661 --> 01:16:09,962
[Daniel] [laughs]
Yeah, that's the best.

1718
01:16:09,995 --> 01:16:11,030
You used to give
a fig, Grandpa.

1719
01:16:11,063 --> 01:16:11,964
[Jack] Oh my goodness.

1720
01:16:11,997 --> 01:16:14,033
I do love it.

1721
01:16:14,066 --> 01:16:16,735
We could be twinsies [laughs]

1722
01:16:16,769 --> 01:16:19,538
[gentle music]

1723
01:16:21,473 --> 01:16:22,875
Cookies, again?

1724
01:16:22,908 --> 01:16:24,476
Yeah!

1725
01:16:24,510 --> 01:16:26,612
You know I wouldn't
mind being with you.

1726
01:16:27,613 --> 01:16:28,614
I gotta go though.

1727
01:16:28,648 --> 01:16:30,482
My dad says we have to be home.

1728
01:16:30,516 --> 01:16:32,851
Linds, before we go,

1729
01:16:32,885 --> 01:16:34,887
could I talk to you
about something?

1730
01:16:34,920 --> 01:16:36,622
Yeah, of course,
babe, what's up?

1731
01:16:38,157 --> 01:16:40,192
I brought you something.

1732
01:16:40,226 --> 01:16:42,662
It's little, but it
means a lot to me.

1733
01:16:45,030 --> 01:16:47,066
Linds, you mean the world to me.

1734
01:16:47,099 --> 01:16:49,301
Since we met at the church,

1735
01:16:49,335 --> 01:16:52,238
you fully restored
faith in my life.

1736
01:16:52,271 --> 01:16:53,707
And not only in my life,

1737
01:16:53,739 --> 01:16:56,676
but we've helped so many
people restore their hope

1738
01:16:56,710 --> 01:16:58,110
and their love.

1739
01:16:59,578 --> 01:17:02,314
Most importantly, we
brought love back to them.

1740
01:17:02,348 --> 01:17:03,549
[air whooshing]

1741
01:17:03,582 --> 01:17:06,686
Mom, how do you know
when it's true love?

1742
01:17:06,720 --> 01:17:09,188
Well, you just know,

1743
01:17:09,221 --> 01:17:10,724
like your dad and I.

1744
01:17:10,756 --> 01:17:13,727
The right person will represent
hope and faith and love.

1745
01:17:15,561 --> 01:17:16,730
I wouldn't worry about that.

1746
01:17:18,732 --> 01:17:21,333
You look so beautiful.
[air whooshing]

1747
01:17:21,367 --> 01:17:22,835
I don't know what to say.

1748
01:17:22,868 --> 01:17:26,238
Linds, when you
wear this necklace,

1749
01:17:27,707 --> 01:17:29,775
I want you to be
reminded of three things.

1750
01:17:31,377 --> 01:17:32,778
The cross represents faith,

1751
01:17:35,247 --> 01:17:36,782
the anchor represents hope,

1752
01:17:38,584 --> 01:17:39,952
and the heart represents love,

1753
01:17:41,120 --> 01:17:42,689
which is everything
you are to me.

1754
01:18:01,840 --> 01:18:04,043
It's beautiful, Andrew.

1755
01:18:04,076 --> 01:18:05,210
You look great in it.

1756
01:18:10,916 --> 01:18:11,984
[Lindsey] Thank
you, I love it.

1757
01:18:12,017 --> 01:18:14,186
[Andrew] You're welcome.

1758
01:18:35,809 --> 01:18:36,909
[gentle music]

1759
01:18:36,942 --> 01:18:38,745
[Lindsey] I
would give anything

1760
01:18:38,778 --> 01:18:40,346
to have my mom here with me.

1761
01:18:45,050 --> 01:18:48,520
For a long time, I was
angry with my own pain.

1762
01:18:49,555 --> 01:18:52,591
Sometimes people grieving, well,

1763
01:18:52,624 --> 01:18:54,193
we get caught up
in our own pain,

1764
01:18:57,896 --> 01:18:59,865
so much so, we can't see

1765
01:18:59,898 --> 01:19:02,935
how serving others
in pain would help,

1766
01:19:02,968 --> 01:19:05,070
or why we should even do it.

1767
01:19:06,338 --> 01:19:10,744
I was just so angry
with life, with God,

1768
01:19:12,878 --> 01:19:15,581
but I grew in my faith.

1769
01:19:19,385 --> 01:19:23,489
I realized that helping
people also helped me heal.

1770
01:19:24,890 --> 01:19:29,194
For me, being able to help
people heal and have faith

1771
01:19:29,228 --> 01:19:32,564
has been the greatest
gift from God.

1772
01:19:40,038 --> 01:19:42,809
I know that a Living
Legacy of Love

1773
01:19:42,842 --> 01:19:44,910
has brought hope
to so many people,

1774
01:19:45,879 --> 01:19:47,379
and it will for years to come.

1775
01:19:48,914 --> 01:19:50,048
Never feel alone.

1776
01:19:51,183 --> 01:19:54,953
Know that God is
always with you.

1777
01:21:26,478 --> 01:21:29,047
[gentle music]

1778
01:21:51,503 --> 01:21:52,371
Hey, Mom.

1779
01:21:56,743 --> 01:21:59,311
First off, I wanna say thank you

1780
01:21:59,344 --> 01:22:02,682
for finally sharing that
secret lasagna recipe with me.

1781
01:22:03,883 --> 01:22:06,886
You made Tony and
my boys so happy.

1782
01:22:08,554 --> 01:22:10,422
Maybe you could make
it for them too.

1783
01:22:13,693 --> 01:22:15,060
I also, I just,

1784
01:22:16,395 --> 01:22:18,564
I wanna say that, that
being your daughter,

1785
01:22:20,065 --> 01:22:21,533
has been such an honor.

1786
01:22:23,569 --> 01:22:25,070
You've always been my hero.

1787
01:22:27,072 --> 01:22:28,440
I hope I've made you proud.

1788
01:22:33,612 --> 01:22:35,715
I'm gonna miss your hugs.

1789
01:22:36,849 --> 01:22:37,717
I'm gonna miss your hugs

1790
01:22:37,750 --> 01:22:40,552
and your weird mom jokes.

1791
01:22:41,921 --> 01:22:44,489
Please tell them to my boys.

1792
01:22:44,523 --> 01:22:46,759
Help them remember who I am.

1793
01:22:46,793 --> 01:22:48,928
And remember that
they're your family too.

1794
01:22:52,197 --> 01:22:57,070
Don't be sad and don't be alone.

1795
01:22:59,104 --> 01:23:00,439
I love you, Mom.

1796
01:23:02,608 --> 01:23:03,542
I love you.

1797
01:23:05,110 --> 01:23:09,716
Carla, this message means
that I'm watching over you.

1798
01:23:12,618 --> 01:23:13,886
Please don't be sad.

1799
01:23:15,554 --> 01:23:17,957
We had 20 beautiful years,

1800
01:23:18,925 --> 01:23:20,760
and three beautiful children.

1801
01:23:23,428 --> 01:23:28,433
I want you to laugh, feel joy,
and tell stories about me,

1802
01:23:29,669 --> 01:23:32,571
so that our children
and our grandchildren

1803
01:23:32,604 --> 01:23:35,173
would know how much I
love you and our family.

1804
01:23:38,845 --> 01:23:41,748
Until we meet again, I
love you, my sweet wife.

1805
01:23:44,616 --> 01:23:47,352
Thank you for so
many wonderful years.

1806
01:23:51,991 --> 01:23:55,862
Oh, honey, I know
you're hurting without me.

1807
01:23:55,895 --> 01:23:57,897
That's why I wanted to
try to do this, a tape,

1808
01:23:57,930 --> 01:23:59,032
while I still could.

1809
01:24:01,834 --> 01:24:03,803
I can't thank you enough

1810
01:24:03,836 --> 01:24:06,739
for being there for
me all these years,

1811
01:24:06,773 --> 01:24:09,142
and facing the big C with me.

1812
01:24:09,174 --> 01:24:10,143
[gentle music]

1813
01:24:10,175 --> 01:24:11,443
I know it wasn't easy.

1814
01:24:14,246 --> 01:24:15,180
How could it be?

1815
01:24:16,983 --> 01:24:21,688
I wasn't always myself
and I'm sorry for that.

1816
01:24:23,690 --> 01:24:24,691
It just wasn't fair.

1817
01:24:27,192 --> 01:24:28,695
But I want you to know

1818
01:24:28,728 --> 01:24:31,798
that you weren't just
the love of my life,

1819
01:24:31,831 --> 01:24:33,298
you were my life,

1820
01:24:33,331 --> 01:24:37,369
and you brought so much joy
and laughter into this family.

1821
01:24:37,402 --> 01:24:41,007
But now it's time for
you to live, baby,

1822
01:24:41,040 --> 01:24:44,110
and share that big, beautiful
light inside of yours,

1823
01:24:44,143 --> 01:24:45,144
with the world.

1824
01:24:46,411 --> 01:24:51,017
Hey, Megs, I know everyone
says this in the movies,

1825
01:24:51,851 --> 01:24:53,452
but if you are watching this,

1826
01:24:56,221 --> 01:24:57,522
I have left this world.

1827
01:25:02,427 --> 01:25:04,362
I wanted to leave you something

1828
01:25:05,765 --> 01:25:10,402
that not only would inspire
you, but comfort you.

1829
01:25:11,838 --> 01:25:13,305
And even though I'm not in
this world with you physically,

1830
01:25:15,340 --> 01:25:17,777
I will always be with you here.

1831
01:25:23,116 --> 01:25:23,916
No tears.

1832
01:25:32,591 --> 01:25:35,661
You have to keep
your chin up, okay?

1833
01:25:35,695 --> 01:25:37,797
You have to be strong
